<!-- body="start" -->
International Society for Traumatic Stress Studies (ISTSS), NY Chapter &amp;<br>
Armenian American Society for Studies on Stress and Genocide (AASSSG), &amp;<br>
Fordham Psychology Association cosponsored a symposium on "Sequelae of<br>
Sociopolitical Violence: Treatment Approaches," at Fordham University, New<br>
York City, on December 13, 1996.  Panel was organized and Chaired by Dr. Anie<br>
Sanentz Kalayjian President of both ISTSS &amp; AASSSG, panelists were:  Mr.<br>
Ernest Duff, M. Div. "The situation in USA," Dr. Anie S. Kalayjian, "The<br>
Azeri-Armenian conflict," Dr. Debora Munczek, "The situation in Honduras,"<br>
Dr. Jack Saul, "The situation in New York."<br>
It was a very stimulating and insightful panel addressing human rights issues<br>
as it relates to pscyhological, emotiona, and spiritual coping. <br>
This panel will be repeated at the United Nations on January 15, 1997,<br>
Wednesday 1:15-2:45 PM, at the United Nations Headquarters in New York City.<br>
 For more information to attend this panel or to become a member of AASSSG or<br>
ISTSS please contact Dr. Anie Sanentz Kalayjian @ (201) 941-2266 or<br>
Kalayjiana@aol.com.  Please be advised that the deadline for the notice is<br>
Jan. 1, 97, as a 2 week notice is essential to obtain security clearance from<br>
the United Nations.<br>
