<title>Groong Network: Yerevan,Baku exchange accusations.....</title>
<h1>Yerevan,Baku exchange accusations.....</h1>
Kevork K. Oskanian (<i>100436.3410@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 16 Dec 1996 11:47:35 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#135">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#135">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#135">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#135">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0136.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (December 16)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0134.html">Chavoush@aol.com: "Armenian News 12/15/96"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
  YEREVAN, December 16 (Itar-Tass) -- Azeri troops opened crossborder <br>
fire at targets in south-western Armenia overnight from Sunday to Monday, <br>
a spokesman for the Armenian defence ministry told Itar-Tass on <br>
Monday. <br>
   According to the spokesman, Azeri units poured machine-gun and tommy-gun<br>
<p>
fire at the village of Tsirani Dzor in Armenia's Syunik region. <br>
   No one was killed or wounded, the spokesman said. The Armenian troops <br>
responded with "adequate retaliatory measures" to suppress the Azeris <br>
gun-fire attack. <br>
   No incidents were reported at other sections of the Azeri-Armenian <br>
border, the spokesman said. <br>
   Meanwhile, reports from Baku said, the Azeri defence ministry refuted <br>
Armenian reports about Azeri gunfire attack across  the border between <br>
the two states. <br>
   The Azeri armed forces "strictly comply with the ceazefire regime in the<br>
<p>
conflict zone and along the Armenian-Azeri borders, agreed upon two and <br>
a half years ago under Russia's mediation," Itar-Tass was told at the <br>
Azeri defence ministry. <br>
   ras/gor <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
