<title>Groong Network: Evaluation of Lisbon Summit results by political parties in</title>
<h1>Evaluation of Lisbon Summit results by political parties in</h1>
Arthur Martirosyan (<i>martiros@hulaw1.harvard.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 15 Dec 1996 23:58:41 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#132">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#132">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#132">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#132">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0133.html">KEVORK: "second messege-NEW ARMENIAN WWW SITE(GREECE)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0131.html">Arthur Martirosyan: "Turkish complicity in March 1995 coup attempt in Baku"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Evaluation of Lisbon Summit results by political parties in Baku<br>
<p>
Baku, December 7, 96 ("Azdlyg")<br>
<p>
The statement of the Party of People's Front of Azerbaijan reads that "the<br>
PPFA prognosis on Lisbon summit results came true that is the summit did not<br>
give anything to Azerbaijan. The Azeri diplomacy once again demonstrated<br>
that it is not capable of resolving the problem." <br>
<p>
The Chairman of the "Mussavat" party Isa Gambar: "The fact that the<br>
concluding declaration did not include a clause on the territorial integrity<br>
of Azerbaijan cannot be evaluated positively. This OSCE summit only<br>
demonstrated its limitations.   <br>
<p>
General Secretary of the Party of National Independence Elshad Musayev: "We<br>
have to provide for the territorial integrity of our country ourselves. For<br>
the purpose of national solidarity reforms shall be accelerated and a strong<br>
national army shall be built." <br>
 <br>
Co-Chairman of the Social-Democratic Party, Zardusht Alizade: "It would be<br>
incorrect to consider that the Lisbon Summit did not give anything to<br>
Azerbaijan. Metaphorically speaking, the summit ended in a draw but our team<br>
dominated in the game."  <br>
<p>
Co-Chairman of the "Vakhdat" Party, Leyla Yunusova: "The Lisbon Summit did<br>
not result in anything new. The existing condition will continue for 10-15<br>
years."  <br>
<p>
Head of the organizational department of the party "new Azerbaijan",<br>
Siyavush Novruzov: "We evaluate results of the Summit fairly high. As a<br>
result of tremendous efforts of our President a statement was made which<br>
reflects our position. The Lisbon Summit ended with a convincing victory of<br>
Azerbaijani diplomacy."  <br>
 <br>
Baku, December 7, 1996 (IA "Turan")<br>
<p>
The Party of Civic Solidarity made a statement expressing party's views on<br>
the results of the Lisbon Summit. The document conveys "a serious concern<br>
with the absence of an article on territorial integrity of Azerbaijan in the<br>
final declaration." One is getting an impression that foreign states do not<br>
intend to recognize Armenia as an aggressor. Meanwhile, foreign countries<br>
are only concerned with their economic interests and therefore are<br>
interested in freezing the conflict, reads the document. The Council of the<br>
Party thinks that it is necessary to introduce military situation, to<br>
reinforce military-patriotic propaganda in mass media and to stop<br>
persecutions on political motives.<br>
<p>
(end) <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
