<title>Groong Network: job opportunity in armenia</title>
<h1>job opportunity in armenia</h1>
Bruce Becker (<i>bmbecker@igc.apc.org</i>)<br>
<i>Sat, 14 Dec 96 15:12:23 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#127">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#127">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#127">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#127">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0128.html">Chavoush@aol.com: "Armenian News 12/14/96"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0126.html">Vatche Gabrielian: "Azeri News"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
AmeriCares, a humanitarian relief organization, in partnership with<br>
the Ministry of Health of Armenia and in collaboration with UNICEF,<br>
will be carrying out a pediatric primary care program in Armenia from<br>
February to August 1997. We are looking for a person to be Project<br>
Director in Country.  The project is in Yerevan and Ararat. The<br>
appropriate person will have a background in health care and<br>
management. There will be extensive logisitical responsibilities. A<br>
rudimentary or better knowledge of Armenian will be a definite<br>
advantage.<br>
If you are interested, please contact me immediately!<br>
<p>
Bruce Becker, M.D.<br>
Department of Emergency Medicine<br>
Rhode Island Hospital<br>
593 Eddy Street<br>
Providence Rhode Island  02903<br>
<p>
401-444-6654<br>
bmbecker@igc.apc.org<br>
