        THE STATEMENT OF THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY OF THE NAGORN0-KARABAGH<br>
        REPUBLIC TRANSMITTED TO A REPRESENTATIVE OF OSCE<br>
<p>
 STEPANAKERT, DECEMBER 13, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, the Head of the Permanent Committee on Foreign Relations<br>
 of the National Assembly of the Nagorno-Karabagh Republic, Vasili<br>
 Atajanian met with the Field Assistant of the Personal Representative<br>
 of the OSCE Acting Chairman, Alexander Vasiliev. Mr. Atajanian gave<br>
 Mr. Vasiliev the text of the December 11 statement of the National<br>
 Assembly of the Nagorno-Karabagh Republic in response to the<br>
 statement of the OSCE Acting Chairman about the principles of the<br>
 Karabagh conflict resolution.<br>
<p>
        CHARITY AND HEALTH FUND'S ACTIVITIES IN 1996<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 13, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 This year, the Charity and Health Fund of Armenia has provided<br>
 humanitarian assistance to 10 martyrs' families, 11 Armenian families<br>
 who suffered in the railroad accident in Bashkiria (Russian<br>
 Federation), and more than 470 disabled persons.<br>
 According to the Chairman of the Fund Narine Balayan, the fund has<br>
 donated diagnostic equipment to the Yerevan Medical University, and<br>
 provided assistance to pensioners and single mothers.<br>
 The fund was established in 1989. It unites more than 1500<br>
 scientists, doctors, teachers and engineers around the country. It<br>
 also has close ties with charitable organizations abroad.<br>
<p>
        STARCH PRODUCTION IN MARTUNI<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 13, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The "Ani" joint-stock company in Martuni has started the production<br>
 of starch. It is the only enterprise in Transcaucasia producing<br>
 starch. It processes 5 tons of potatos per hour, which yields 800 kg<br>
 of starch.<br>
 The profitability of the enterprise is not high (only 4%). However,<br>
 it solves some major problems. First of all, it buys large quantities<br>
 of potatos produced in the region, thus sparing the farmers lots of<br>
 troubles related to the selling of their produce. Second, it gives<br>
 employment to many people (workers of "Ani" who were left<br>
 unemployed).<br>
<p>
        AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE CENTRAL BANK OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA<br>
        AND THE INTERSTATE BANK SIGNED IN YEREVAN<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 13, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The President of the Central Bank of the Republic of Armenia Bagrat<br>
 Asatrian and the President of the Interstate Bank Vladimir Mashits<br>
 signed today an agreement on opening correspondent accounts.<br>
 The Interstate Bank was established in 1993 by a special agreement of<br>
 the leaders of the CIS countries (except Azerbaijan and Georgia). The<br>
 governments and the central banks of the participating countries are<br>
 the founders of the Bank. The original purpose of the Bank was to<br>
 enhance trade and facilitate transactions between the participating<br>
 countries.<br>
 The President of the Central Bank of the Republic of Armenia Bagrat<br>
 Asatrian stated in a press conference after signing the agreement,<br>
 that the Interstate Bank has been a mere formal organization, but he<br>
 expressed his hope that the newly signed agreement will become a<br>
 basis for real cooperation.<br>
 The President of the Interstate Bank said that soon a representation<br>
 of the Bank will open in Yerevan. This will activate the cooperation.<br>
 Mr. Mashits also informed the journalists that he has proposed to<br>
 increase the founding capital of the Bank from 5 billion roubles to<br>
 65 billion roubles. He said that currently this proposal is being<br>
 negotiated.<br>
<p>
        NEW ORGANIZATIONS AND MEANS OF MASS MEDIA REGISTERED<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 13, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Armenia has registered new<br>
 organizations: League of Women Voters, "Meknutyun" psychological<br>
 research center, Armenian branch of the International Academy of<br>
 Mineral Resources, Armenian brach of the International Association of<br>
 Energy Sector Engineers, Educational and Cultural Exchange Programs<br>
 Union, Union for Defense of the Rights of Refugees.<br>
 The Ministry also registered the "Bulletin of State Employees,"<br>
 "Armenian Forest," and  "Zartonk" magazines, "Burg" radiostation, and<br>
 "Ara" TV studio in Armavir.<br>
