<title>Groong Network: Segodnya on Ciller-Catli affair</title>
<h1>Segodnya on Ciller-Catli affair</h1>
Arthur Martirosyan (<i>martiros@hulaw1.harvard.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 13 Dec 1996 15:49:08 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#112">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#112">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#112">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#112">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0113.html">Arthur Martirosyan: "From Monitor"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0111.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (December 13)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Segodnya, N231, December 11, 96<br>
<p>
Sensational Accusations Against Tansu Ciller<br>
<p>
A report to the current Prime Minister of Turkey Necmettin Erbakan on former<br>
Prime Minister and acting Foreign Affairs Minister Tansu Ciller's spending<br>
of 250 billion TL ($250,000) from a secret government fund has had an effect<br>
of a bomb explosion in Ankara.  According to the report, Prime Minister used<br>
that money for training of professional assassins hired to kill Abdullah<br>
Ocalan, the leader of the PKK.  The money was given to Abdullah Catli,<br>
leader of one of the mafia gangs, who was wanted by Interpol. In early<br>
November he died in an accident in the same car with a member of the<br>
Parliament from Ciller's True Path Party and officer of secret services. The<br>
accident was the prime reason for an investigation into penetration of the<br>
mafia octopus into government structures of Turkey.  <br>
<p>
The document indicates that the operation aimed at elimination of the leader<br>
of separatists, who have been fighting to build an independent Kurdish state<br>
in the south east of Turkey for many years now, was conducted without<br>
informing the Interior Minister, National Intelligence organization and<br>
General Staff. The operation was prevented only after Turkish intelligence<br>
service had interfered to warn Ciller about deficiencies in the operation<br>
planning.  The report also asserts that Catli's gangs were trained by<br>
instructors from Israeli Mossad  and were used by Tel Aviv in several<br>
actions against Palestinians. The gangs were involved in drug trafficking<br>
and control over illegal gambling business. (end) <br>
<p>
(Translated by AM. Names transliterated from Russian.) <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
