<title>Groong Network: ADMINISTRATIVE NOTICE - Do not delete.</title>
<h1>ADMINISTRATIVE NOTICE - Do not delete.</h1>
Groong/Hayastan Administrator (<i>asbed@skat.usc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 12 Dec 96 19:04:11 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#109">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#109">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#109">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#109">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0110.html">vahe@arminco.com: "Aragil Headlines, 12/13/96"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0108.html">Armen Martirossyan: "From Armenpress homepage"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Dear Groong and Hayastan readers,<br>
<p>
Two days ago I presented to you a project to fund - subscribing Groong<br>
to Noyan Tapan. If you're subscribed to Groong today and you like it,<br>
you will be infinitely more please with Noyan Tapan's excellent news<br>
coming to you daily.<br>
<p>
Unfortunately, out of 1150 readers on Groong and 350 participants on<br>
Hayastan, I've only heard from 66 people today, pledging to fund the<br>
subscription to NT. That's about 5% participation and truly deplorable.<br>
I can't believe that 95% of the lists' audiences DO NOT CARE about<br>
improving the content of our news list.<br>
<p>
Ladies and gentlemen, I believe this is an excellent opportunity which WE<br>
CAN NOT PASS ON. I urge you to please respond to me immediately, if you<br>
haven't already, and pledge your support for improved future news<br>
reception and sources. The sooner we're done, the sooner we'll begin<br>
receiving news from Noyan Tapan.<br>
<p>
I'm including the text of the original proposal. I hope to hear from<br>
a strong number of you very soon.<br>
<p>
Sincerely,<br>
<p>
Asbed<br>
=====<br>
	Proposal for funding of Noyan Tapan Acquisition.<br>
<p>
Dear Hayastan and Groong readers,<br>
<p>
We've been in touch with Noyan Tapan (NT) to acquire their news on a daily<br>
basis for Groong. As you may already know, NT is based in Armenia and<br>
sells its news service for a fee.<br>
<p>
NT came forward voluntarily during September's elections in Armenia and<br>
informed us with up-to-the-minute news and events for altruistic reasons.<br>
We appreciated their work; we think that their news service is very<br>
informative and timely, and we'd like to read more of it, and regularly.<br>
<p>
Noyan Tapan has requested a fee of $250/month for a specially prepared<br>
"Groong Edition" daily bulletin, and has sent us many days' worth of<br>
samples. I'm attaching one day's worth below for your perusal and<br>
judgement. I feel the fee is reasonable and well worth it.<br>
<p>
In addition to improving our quality of news here on Groong, and being<br>
better informed on Armenia and the Caucasus region in general, our<br>
subscription to Noyan Tapan will be an explicit statement of support<br>
and approval for free and independent media in Armenia.<br>
<p>
As the daily readers of Groong News, there's only you to turn to, to fund<br>
such a project. Therefore I'm asking all interested parties to come<br>
forward with any amount of donation to fund the next 12 months' worth of<br>
Noyan Tapan reception on Groong.<br>
<p>
We need to raise $3000 for this. Groong has 1100 members and Hayastan<br>
has 350. If 100 members come forward with $30 each, we're there! If<br>
more members come forward, then we will arrange to receive as many<br>
more months of daily Noyan Tapan as we have money for.  And if we<br>
don't come up with the required funds, then I will assume that we're<br>
not interested in receiving Noyan Tapan daily.<br>
<p>
I ask that you send me email, with your pledge amount, which I will<br>
tally. The deadline for this initial drive is December 25. If we're<br>
well on the way, I'll extend the deadline a bit and continue reminding<br>
very often, as I feel that this is a very worthy service and would<br>
enhance our news from Armenia greatly.  I will of course update the<br>
list very regularly of our progress. In fact, I can tell you that we<br>
already have $260 from just 4 Groong readers!<br>
<p>
My goal at the moment is to receive NT news daily for all of 1997.<br>
<p>
Send no money now. Once final amounts are tallied, I'll inform the lists<br>
where to send checks and who to write it out to. As far as trusting that<br>
your (our) funds will be well used, I assure you that every penny will<br>
be spent on this project, and there will be not a penny of administrative<br>
overheard (I'll deal with that).<br>
<p>
I hope to hear from you very soon. Please help if you can.<br>
<p>
Regards,<br>
<p>
Asbed<br>
