<title>Groong Network: New Armenian site on the WWW</title>
<h1>New Armenian site on the WWW</h1>
armen-info.com (<i>72263.1572@CompuServe.COM</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 12 Dec 96 14:20:05 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#106">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#106">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#106">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#106">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0107.html">ASBAREZ-ON-LINE: "ASBAREZ-ON-LINE [12-12-96]"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0105.html">Asbed Bedrossian: "AP/Reuters headlines to 12/12/96"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<a href="http://armen-info.com">http://armen-info.com</a><br>
<p>
At the Armen-Info site you will find bilingual (English and French) information<br>
on Armenia, Armenians and almost everything Armenian, with a special attention<br>
to Canadian-Armenian facts and issues.<br>
<p>
Au site Armen-Info, vous trouverez des informations bilingues (anglais et<br>
francais) sur lArmenie, les armeniens et sur pratiquement tout ce qui leur<br>
concerne, portant surtout attention aux faits canadiens-armeniens.<br>
<p>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<p>
Hosted on armen-info.com are:<br>
<p>
a) Nouvelles en francais GAMK/HORIZON, provenant de Gamk, un quotidien bilingue<br>
de Paris, France, et de lhebdomadaire trilingue, Horizon de Montreal, Canada.<br>
Les nouvelles seront mises a jour trois fois par semaine: les lundis, mercredis<br>
et vendredis.<br>
<p>
b) Horizon Online: The WWW version of the English supplement of<br>
Horizon Weekly, a Canadian-Armenian trilingual newspaper, published by the Les<br>
Publications<br>
Armeniennes of Montreal, Quebec. Horizon Online provides news and information<br>
on Canadian-Armenian events and personalities; furthermore, it hosts<br>
information, analysis and<br>
commentary on Armenian issues around the world. Horizon Online is updated<br>
regularly on every<br>
Thursday. Special bulletins are posted if the need arises.<br>
<p>
c) The Armenian Cause: The billingual (English &amp; French) quarterly newsletter,<br>
published by the Armenian National Committee of Canada (ANCC), since 1984.<br>
Contains a large amount of information about the Armenian Cause, the Armenian<br>
Genocide, the conflict of Nagorno-Karabagh and other related events of the last<br>
twelve years.<br>
<p>
d) La Cause Armenienne: Ce bulletin bilingue est publie par le Comite national<br>
armenien du Canada (CNAC), depuis avril, 1984.  Contienent des informations<br>
cruciales sur la cause armenienne, le genocide armenien, les conflits a<br>
Haut-Karabagh, pour en nommer quelques-unes.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
