<title>Groong Network: Armenian Church leader visits pope</title>
<h1>Armenian Church leader visits pope</h1>
Kevork K. Oskanian (<i>100436.3410@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 11 Dec 96 12:47:34 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#94">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#94">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#94">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#94">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0095.html">Kevork K. Oskanian: "Crime links probed in Turkey"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0093.html">Kevork K. Oskanian: "VOA/Turkey/Military"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
    VATICAN CITY (Reuter) - Pope John Paul II Wednesday welcomed<br>
to the Vatican the spiritual leader of the world's six million<br>
Armenian Christians, Karekin I, who is on a five-day official<br>
visit.<br>
     The two, the Pope wearing his traditional white cassock and<br>
the bearded Karekin wearing a hooded black robe, sat side by<br>
side on identical thrones during the Pope's general audience.<br>
     The Armenian Church is one of the so-called Ancient Churches<br>
of the East which split from Byzantine Christianity before the<br>
Great Schism of 1054 that divided the Eastern and Western<br>
Churches.<br>
     The Pope told the crowd in the Vatican's audience hall that<br>
he hoped the two Churches could eventually reach full unity.<br>
     Karekin said he was praying for the 76-year-old Pope's good<br>
health, "not only for the good of the Roman Catholic Church but<br>
for that of all humanity."<br>
     The Armenian Church is an independent Christian Church<br>
introduced to Armenia by the apostles Jude and Bartholomew. In<br>
301 A.D. Armenia became the first nation to adopt Christianity<br>
as a state religion.<br>
     The Armenian Church has various patriarchates around the<br>
world and members in the countries of the former Soviet Union,<br>
North and South America, the Middle East, Europe and Asia.<br>
 REUTER<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
