     <br>
     EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY<br>
     <br>
     The Armenian Assembly of America seeks a mature and motivated <br>
     self-starter to fill the Assistant Director of ARAMAC <br>
     (Armenian-American Action Committee) position. The successful <br>
     applicant will assist the Director in notifying the nationwide, <br>
     grassroots network of pertinent legislative and anti-defamation <br>
     issues, maintaining publications, and organizing and managing all <br>
     facets of the Armenian Assembly Summer Internship Program. <br>
     <br>
     Candidates should have: Capitol Hill and/or grassroots development <br>
     experience; excellent organizational, communication, and computer <br>
     skills; ability to balance several high priority projects  <br>
     simultaneously; initiative; and flexibility. Knowledge of the <br>
     Armenian-American community is desirable, but not required.<br>
     <br>
     Salary commensurate with qualifications.<br>
     Available: Immediately. <br>
     <br>
     Fax or mail resume and cover letter to:<br>
     <br>
     fax:  (202) 638-4904<br>
     <br>
     Armenian Assembly of America<br>
     Arpi Vartanian, ARAMAC Director<br>
     122 C. Street, N.W.   Suite 350<br>
     Washington, D.C.   20001<br>
     <br>
     Please do not e-mail your resume. <br>
