<title>Groong Network: Armenian High Court sentences party activists to death</title>
<h1>Armenian High Court sentences party activists to death</h1>
Kevork K. Oskanian (<i>100436.3410@CompuServe.COM</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 10 Dec 96 16:16:30 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#83">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#83">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#83">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#83">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0084.html">Chavoush@aol.com: "Armenian News 12/10/96"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Armen Martirossyan: "From Armenpress homepage"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
    YEREVAN (Reuter) - Armenia's Supreme Court on Tuesday<br>
sentenced three members of the outlawed Dashnaktsitun political<br>
party to death on terrorism charges.<br>
     Judge Eduard Manukyan said Armen Mndjoyan, Arsen Arsrune and<br>
Armen Grigoryan would be put to death for terrorist activities,<br>
drugs trafficking, and arms dealing.<br>
     Lawyers for the condemned immediately said they planned to<br>
appeal. Eight other members of the nationalist party got<br>
sentences of three to 15 years in prison.<br>
     Dashnaktsitun was outlawed in 1994 by President Levon<br>
Ter-Petrosyan who said its members were plotting terrorist acts<br>
and wanted to overthrow the government.<br>
     But Dashnaktsitun maintained it was the victim of a witchunt<br>
to crack down on dissent in the small Caucasus state of three<br>
and a half million.<br>
     Ter-Petrosyan closed several opposition parties earlier this<br>
year and sent tanks into the streets after he won a<br>
controversial second term in office. International observers<br>
said the vote was marred by major violations.<br>
  REUTER<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
