<!-- body="start" -->
        LARGE HOTELS TO BE PRIVATIZED THROUGH INTERNATIONAL<br>
TENDER<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 9, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 According to the Deputy Minister of Trade, Services, and Tourism of<br>
 the Republic of Armenia Hrant Margarian, 2200 enterprises formerly<br>
 belonging to the Ministry are waiting to be privatized. 2370 more<br>
 enterprises are scheduled to be privatized by the 1996-1997<br>
 privatization program. "Armenia," "Dvin" and "Ani" hotels (largest<br>
 hotels in Yerevan), will be privatized through an international<br>
 tender.<br>
<p>
        THREE TYPES OF ACTIVITIES OF THE MINISTRY OF SOCIAL<br>
WELFARE<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 9, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 During a press conference, the Minister of Social Welfare of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia Ms. Hranush Hakobian said that the Ministry will<br>
 engage in activities in three main directions: employment, pensions,<br>
 and social assistance programs. Talking about the employment, Ms.<br>
 Hakobian said that it is necessary to develop appropriate state and<br>
 regional programs, to study the job market, to increase the<br>
 professional qualifications of the unemployed, and to encourage<br>
 small and middle scale businesses.<br>
 As for the pensions, Ms. Hakobian said that the Ministry of Social<br>
 Welfare only determines the size of the pensions and who is to<br>
 receive a pensions. Then, the responsibility for delivering the<br>
 pensions is on the Pension Fund, the cashiers, and the persons who<br>
 deliver the pensions. This is where all the delays in pension<br>
 payments occur.<br>
 As one of the main priorities of the Ministry, Ms. Hakobian pointed<br>
 out the determination of the real social situation in the country and<br>
 finding the people who really need help from the government.<br>
<p>
        AZERI OPPOSITION DISSATISFIED WITH THE RESULTS OF THE<br>
OSCE LISBON SUMMIT<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 9, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The results of the OSCE Lisbon Summit have created a wave of<br>
 dissatisfaction in Azerbaijan. It is stated in the statement of the<br>
 Popular Front (opposition party in Azerbaijan) that the Summit has<br>
 demonstrated the incompetence of the Azeri diplomacy.<br>
 According to the Popular Front, the OSCE is indifferent to the<br>
 internationally acknowledged principle of preservation of territorial<br>
 integrity.<br>
 "The hesitation of the Azeri government resulted in Azerbaijan's<br>
 backing up before pressure, and the aggressor kept its position to<br>
 the end,"- says the statement.<br>
 "In the conditions of corruption and protectionism, limitation of the<br>
 human rights and democratic norms, the foreign politics of a country<br>
 can not be successful," concluded the statement.<br>
<p>
        ARMENIA MAY BECOME A MEMBER OF THE WORLD TRADE<br>
ORGANIZATION<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 9, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 It is very likely that next year Armenia will become a full member of<br>
 the World Trade Organization. This means that the Republic will<br>
 established a special kind of commercial relations with 120-130<br>
 countries.<br>
 However, according to the Deputy Minister of Economy of the Republic<br>
 of Armenia Vardan Movsissian, this membership is a necessary, but not<br>
 sufficient condition for entering the international market.<br>
 According to Mr. Movsissian, it is necessary to strengthen the<br>
 industry and raise the quality of production to international<br>
 standards before Armenia can enter international trade.<br>
<p>
<p>
        MEETINGS WITH THE PRESIDENT TER-PETROSSIAN<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 7, the President of the Republic of Armenia Levon<br>
 Ter-Petrossian received the Chairman of the Union of Manufacturers<br>
 and Business People of the Republic of Armenia Aram Vardanian. The<br>
 sides discussed issues related to the Union's activities and the<br>
 relations between the Union and the Government of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia.<br>
 On December 8, the President of the Republic of Armenia Levon<br>
 Ter-Petrossian met with the President of the Nagorno-Karabagh<br>
 Republic Robert Kocharian. During the meeting the sides discussed the<br>
 results of the Lisbon Summit and the present state of the process of<br>
 negotiations of the Karabagh conflict settlement.<br>
 The Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Armenia Alexander<br>
 Arzumanian and the Senior Advisor to the Armenian President Jirair<br>
 Libaridian participated in the meeting.<br>
<p>
        LEONARD PETROSSIAN APPOINTED PRIME MINISTER OF<br>
        NAGORNO-KARABAGH REPUBLIC<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The President of the Nagorno-Karabagh Republic Robert Kocharian<br>
 appointed Mr. Leonard Petrossian to the post of the Prime Minister of<br>
 the Nagorno-Karabagh Republic. Within ten days, the Prime Minister<br>
<p>
 will have to form a Cabinet of Ministers.<br>
<p>
        CIS IS 5 YEARS-OLD<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The December 8 marks the 5th anniversary of CIS. In 1991, leaders of<br>
 Russia, Belorussia, and Ukraine proclaimed the Commonwealth of<br>
 Independent States. On December 21, in Alma-Ata, 11 more countries<br>
 joined the Commonwealth.<br>
 Armenia remains an acitive member of CIS. According to the Ministry<br>
 of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Armenia, Armenia has signed<br>
 more than 50 cooperation agreements, which enhance the integration<br>
 within the CIS.<br>
<p>
<p>
        DELEGATION OF THE ARMENIAN NATIONAL ASSEMBLY VISITS<br>
TBILISI<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Today, a delegation of the National Assembly of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia headed by the President of the National Assembly Babken<br>
 Ararktsian left for Tbilisi, where it will participate in the 8th<br>
 session of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Black Sea Economic<br>
 Cooperation.<br>
 During the visit, the President of the National Assembly of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia Babken Arartsian is expected to meet with the<br>
 President of Georgia Eduard Shevardnadze.<br>
<p>
        SPIRITUAL LEADER OF THE CAUCASIAN MUSLIMS PROPOSES TO<br>
RENAME<br>
        STEPANAKERT TO HEIDARABAD<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 It appears that Azerbaijan has started to undertake a series of<br>
 measures directed towards the creation of guarantees of highest<br>
 autonomy of Nagorny Karabagh within Azerbaijan. As one of the first<br>
 measures, it is proposed to rename the capital of Nagorny Karabagh,<br>
 Stepanakert. The Chairman of the Supreme Spiritual Council of Muslims<br>
 in Caucasus, sheik Ul Islam Haji Allahshukyur Pashazadeh, during a<br>
 meeting with the Azeri President, proposed to change the name of<br>
 Stepanakert to Heidarabad, in honor of the President Heidar Aliev,<br>
 "for the latter's victory during the Lisbon Summit." This was<br>
 reported by the Azeri service of the "Liberty" radio station.<br>
<p>
        "STONE AND SILICATES" FIRM TO ENTER THE INTERNATIONAL<br>
MARKET<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The "Stone and Silicates" research and manufacturing firm has<br>
 completed the development of programs of production based on local<br>
 non-metallic raw materials. According to this program, it is possible<br>
 to produce building materials using the low cost local raw materials.<br>
 The building materials will then be exported to Georgia and Northern<br>
 Caucasus. Several agreements have already been reached to export<br>
 Armenian liquid glass, stone dust, and other materials.<br>
 In order to get financing, this program proposal will be submitted to<br>
 the TACIS (Technical Assistance to CIS) office.<br>
<p>
        VERDICT REACHED IN THE "DRO" CASE<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Today, the Board of Judges of the Supreme Court of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia has announced its verdict in the "Dro" case. Arsen Artsruni,<br>
 Armenak Mnjoyan, and Armen Grigorian are sentenced to death.<br>
 Armenak Zakarian is sentenced to 15, Hovhanes Mkrtchian - to 10, Ara<br>
 Harmandayan - to 6, Edik Simonian - to 5, Gevorg Alaverdian and Tatul<br>
 Gabrielian - to 3 years in prison.<br>
 The Board of Judges that the connection of Hrant Margarian and<br>
 Gegham Manukian to the "Dro" group is not proven. H. Margarian is<br>
 sentenced to 5 years in prison for illegal possession of arms and<br>
 false passport. G. Manukian is sentenced to 3 years in prison for<br>
 being informed about the existence of the armed group and the murder<br>
 and not reporting it.<br>
 This verdict can be appealed to the Presidium of the Supreme Court<br>
 within 7 days.<br>
<p>
        DECLARATIONS OF EXPENSES ON ELECTION CAMPAIGN FOR THE<br>
        RECENT PRESIDENTIAL ELECTIONS<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 10, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The presidential candidates Vazgen Manukian, Sergey Badalian, and the<br>
 elected President Levon Ter-Petrossian submitted the declaration<br>
 about the expenses of their election campaign funds to the Central<br>
 Electoral Commission, as required by the law on Electing the<br>
 President of the Republic.<br>
 According to the submitted declaration, Sergey Badalian spent<br>
 2,713,730 drams on his election campaign (1USD=435 drams), including<br>
 945,430 drams for air time on national radio and television, 139,100<br>
 drams for transportation costs, and 1,629,200 drams for videoclip and<br>
 campaign posters.<br>
 Vazgen Manukian's campaign fund was 1,200,000 drams, of which<br>
408,000<br>
 drams were spent for publishing his election program in the "HaiEdit"<br>
 publishing house, and 792,000 - for publishing the program in "Voskan<br>
 Yerevantsi publishing house. The remaining 130,850 drams will be<br>
 transferred to the National Democratic Union party's bank account.<br>
 The declaration of expenses of the Levon Ter-Petrossian's election<br>
 campaign fund is much more detailed.<br>
 According to the declaration, 191,241,120 drams were deposited in the<br>
 fund. From this amount, 62,296,032 drams were spent on the election<br>
 campaign. The remaining amount is 128,945,088 drams.<br>
 674880 drams were transferred to the State Television Company for<br>
 montage and video recording, 200,000 drams - to the "Hayastani<br>
 Hanrapetutyun" daily newspaper for publishing campaign materials in<br>
 its September 21 issue, 648,000 drams - for the publication of the<br>
 "Paikar" magazine, 1,440,000 drams for the 180 minutes of air-time on<br>
 national television,1,869,140 drams for organizing concerts and<br>
 autoservice, and 1,900,000 drams - for the campaign in the provinces of<br>
 the country.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
