<!-- body="start" -->
     FIRE DESTROYS CHURCH PROPERTY IN ISTANBUL  <br>
     <br>
     ISTANBUL ("Lraper" 6 December 1996)-- Last Thursday afternoon, a large <br>
     fire in the Kumkapi district of Istanbul destroyed three ancient <br>
     buildings, all dating  back to the 1880s, and caused damage to the <br>
     property of Holy Astvadzadzin Armenian Church.<br>
      <br>
     As there was shortage of electric power in the Kumkapi district, where <br>
     the Armenian Patriarchate of Istanbul is located, at sunset, an <br>
     Armenian elderly woman lit a candle in her apartment, which then set <br>
     the curtains on fire. The fire quickly spread and, within a short <br>
     period of time, caused irreparable damages to the buildings.<br>
     <br>
     All three buildings were inhabited by the elderly widows of the <br>
     Armenian community in Istanbul.  So far there are no estimates as to <br>
     the cost of the damages caused by the fire. <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
