<!-- body="start" -->
3. Vardan Oskanian: Armenia Won't Accept Any Pressure<br>
-----------------------------------------------------<br>
   Deputy Foreign Minister's Comments About The OSCE Lisbon Summit<br>
<p>
     YEREVAN  ("Azg"  daily),  12/07/96  --  ROA  Deputy  Foreign <br>
Minister Vardan Oskanian, who actively participated in the  whole <br>
course  of  negotiations,  declared  in  a   meeting   with   the <br>
journalists yesterday that it is hard to predict whether the OSCE <br>
Lisbon Summit will have positive or negative consequences. <br>
     Oskanian believes that it is not clear yet what  conclusions <br>
will Azerbaijan and other OSCE  member-countries  make,  or  what <br>
positions will they accept now. Only then we'll be able to  speak <br>
about the possible developments of the next few months. <br>
     Deputy Foreign Minister stressed that  pressing  has  always <br>
existed, and this line will probably continue, but  Armenia  will <br>
not accept forced actions. One of the important  results  of  the <br>
Lisbon Summit was that Armenia clearly  defined  once  again  the <br>
limits, when no further concessions are possible. <br>
     Oskanian added that a new stage of  negotiations  will  only <br>
start after the problem of the new co-chairmen of Minsk group  is <br>
resolved, but the mediators may be  visiting  the  sides  of  the <br>
conflict during this period. <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
