<!-- body="start" -->
     CATHOLICOS KAREKIN I TO MEET POPE JOHN PAUL II<br>
     <br>
     LONDON (Lraper 6/12/96)--Catholicos Karekin I of All Armenians is due <br>
     to pay an official visit to the Vatican on December 10.  This is the <br>
     first meeting between Karekin I, as Catholicos of All Armenians, and <br>
     Pope John Paul II.  Archbishop Torkom Manoogian and Archbishop Karekin <br>
     Kazanjian, the respective Patriarchates of Jerusalem and <br>
     Constantinople will accompany the Catholicos during the visit, <br>
     together with other high ranking Armenian clergymen.<br>
     <br>
     The last meeting of the heads of the Armenian and the Roman Catholic <br>
     Churches was in 1968 when Catholicos Vazken I met with Pope Paul VI in <br>
     the Vatican. <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
