<!-- body="start" -->
Armenian National Committee of America<br>
888 17th Street, NW, Suite 904<br>
Washington, DC, 20006<br>
Tel. (202) 775-1918<br>
Fax (202) 775-5648<br>
E-mail: anca-dc@ix.netcom.com<br>
<p>
PRESS RELEASE<br>
<p>
For Immediate Release<br>
Contact: Elizabeth S. Chouldjian<br>
December 6, 1996<br>
Tel: (202) 775-1918<br>
<p>
ANCA ISSUES STATEMENT ON THE OSCE LISBON SUMMIT<br>
<p>
WASHINGTON, DC - The Armenian National Committee of America (ANCA) <br>
today released the following statement regarding the position on <br>
Nagorno Karabagh adopted by the Republic of Armenia during the <br>
recently concluded summit of the Organization for Security and <br>
Cooperation in Europe in Lisbon, Portugal.  The final summit <br>
document did not mention Karabagh after Armenia threatened to veto <br>
language which indicated that the Karabagh should be subordinate to <br>
Azerbaijani sovereignty.<br>
__________________________________________________________________<br>
<p>
ANCA STATEMENT ON OSCE LISBON SUMMIT<br>
<p>
We welcome the stand in defense of Nagorno Karabagh adopted by the <br>
Republic of Armenia during the recently concluded Lisbon summit of <br>
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe.<br>
<p>
Exercising its right to veto language in the final summit <br>
declaration, the Armenian government prevented the ratification, by <br>
the OSCE, of the Azerbaijani position that the Republic of Nagorno <br>
Karabagh would be subordinate to Azerbaijani sovereignty.  This <br>
action was fully consistent with previous decisions adopted by the <br>
Armenian Parliament.<br>
<p>
We share the Armenian government's view that the only guarantee for <br>
the security of Nagorno Karabagh is its right to self-<br>
determination.  Any resolution to the conflict which does not fully <br>
respect this right will lead to increased regional instability and <br>
will place the Armenian population of Karabagh under the constant <br>
threat of genocide.<br>
<p>
In remaining committed to Karabagh's right to self-determination, <br>
the Republic of Armenia resisted heavy pressures from Western <br>
states and the countries of the region.  In the wake of this <br>
summit, these pressures will surely increase, fueled by the short-<br>
sighted efforts of the Caspian oil lobby.  This fact was evident in <br>
the decidedly unbalanced statement of the Swiss OSCE Chairman-in-<br>
Office, which called for Nagorno Karabagh to be placed under <br>
Azerbaijani rule.<br>
<p>
We are confident that the collective leadership of the Armenian <br>
nation will rise to meet and overcome these challenges.  Working <br>
together, the Armenian government, the government of Nagorno <br>
Karabagh, and the Diaspora are capable of countering the powerful <br>
interests arrayed against the Armenian nation.  We, therefore, call <br>
on all Armenian American organizations to join together, in <br>
constructive partnership, to advance the commonly held concerns of <br>
all Armenians, and to stand in solidarity with the people of <br>
Nagorno Karabagh.<br>
<p>
#####<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
