<title>Groong Network: Six Rose and Alex Pilibos Alumni Pass the Bar</title>
<h1>Six Rose and Alex Pilibos Alumni Pass the Bar</h1>
Rose & Alex Pilibos (<i>pilibos@planetworks.net</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 6 Dec 96 12:45:05 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#49">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#49">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#49">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#49">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0050.html">ANCA-DC: "ANCA: OSCE ISSUES STATEMENT ON OSCE LISBON SUMMIT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0048.html">Asbed Bedrossian: "Istanbul Editor Dies"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Recently, the July 1996 California Bar Examination pass list was released<br>
by the State Bar of California. The statistics released indicate that six<br>
alumni of Rose and Alex Pilibos Armenian School were among those admitted<br>
to the State Bar. All were taking the Bar Examination for the first time.<br>
Anahid Gerovian, Raffi Shahinian, Karine Tebelekian, Taleen Simon, and<br>
Arsen Shaghig, all from the class of 1988 (representing 100 percent of<br>
students from that class who went to law school) and Harout Balian, a 1987<br>
graduate, were admitted to the Bar. <br>
<p>
"The sound academic base acquired by these students at Pilibos has<br>
undoubtedly served as a propelling force for their impressive achievement<br>
on the Bar," said Mr. Viken Yacoubian, principal of Rose and and Alex<br>
Pilibos Armenian School. "This group of our alumni represents approximately<br>
20% of the total number of Armenians who passed the July 1996 California<br>
Bar Examination. Of course, we are extremely  proud of them" added Mr.<br>
Yacoubian.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
