<title>Groong Network: Vatican Delegation in Istanbul</title>
<h1>Vatican Delegation in Istanbul</h1>
Asbed Bedrossian (<i>asbed@skat.usc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 6 Dec 96 12:39:32 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#47">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#47">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#47">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#47">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0048.html">Asbed Bedrossian: "Istanbul Editor Dies"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0046.html">H.TCHILINGIRIAN@lse.ac.uk: "CORRECTION: Armenian Church in Turkey"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
ISTANBUL ("Lraper" 5 December 1996) - A Vatican delegation headed by<br>
Cardinal Edward Cassidy, president of the Vatican's Pontifical Council<br>
for the Unity of Christians, visited His Beatitude Karekin II,<br>
Armenian Patriarch of Istanbul.<br>
<p>
Accompanying the Cardinal were Bishops Pierre Duprey and Jean-Calude<br>
Tessitet, both Vatican officials, Arcbishop Pier Luigi Celata, Vatican<br>
Ambassador in Ankara, and Mons. Georges Marovitch of the same Embassy.<br>
<p>
The consultation during the ecumenical visit focused on the bilateral <br>
relations between the Roman Catholic and Armenian Apostolic Orthodox <br>
Churches, and the upcoming visit of His Holiness Catholicos Karekin I of <br>
All Armenians to Pope John Paull II, between December 10 and 14. The<br>
Armenian Patriarchs of Istanbul and Jerusalem will be accompanying the <br>
Catholicos.<br>
<p>
The Vatican delegation was in Istanbul for the Orthodox Feast of Saint<br>
Andrew - the patron saint of the Istanbul Church.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
