<!-- body="start" -->
  	       The Armenian Relief Society of North America <br>
 	  <br>
 	       25th Annual Armenian Summer Studies Program  <br>
 			 <br>
 			  July 20-August 9, 1997 <br>
 <br>
 <br>
 		    Bradford College, Bradford, MA.<br>
 <br>
 The three-week program features intensive instruction in Armenian<br>
 language, Armenian history, literature, film, art, dance , and music.<br>
 <br>
 Room and board and tuition are covered by the ARS of North<br>
 America. Applicants are required to pay a non-refundable registration<br>
 fee.<br>
 <br>
 Students must be 18-25 years old and have graduated from high school<br>
 to apply.<br>
 <br>
 	  For more information and applications call or write:<br>
 			 ARS of North America, Inc.<br>
 			      80 Bigelow Ave.<br>
 			     Watertown, MA 02172-2012<br>
 			      (617) 926-3801<br>
 			      or FAX (617)924-7238<br>
