<title>Groong Network: More on Lisbon summit</title>
<h1>More on Lisbon summit</h1>
Arthur Martirosyan (<i>martiros@hulaw1.harvard.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 4 Dec 1996 19:13:30 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#28">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#28">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#28">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#28">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0029.html">Arthur Martirosyan: "Some details on Lisbon summit statement"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0027.html">ASBAREZ-ON-LINE: "ASBAREZ-ON-LINE [12-04-96]"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
ITAR-TASS News Agency<br>
December 03, 1996<br>
<p>
  LISBON, December 3 (Itar-Tass) - "I hope that Armenian and Azerbaijani <br>
leaders will use the Lisbon summit and continue settlement talks with <br>
due account of the opinion of leaders of the OSCE member-countries," <br>
Russian Prime Minister and head of the Russian delegation to the OSCE <br>
Lisbon summit meeting told correspondents before his departure on <br>
Tuesday evening. <br>
<p>
"Unfortunately, not all the documents were adopted at the Lisbon summit <br>
as we would like them to" because of different stands of Armenia and <br>
Azerbaijan on Nagorno-Karabakh, said the prime minister. "But there was <br>
a consensus even in that situation." <br>
<p>
Item 20 of the summit's final declaration was put outside the document <br>
limits, and a statement of the OSCE executive chairman was circulated <br>
instead of this item to outline fundamental settlement principles. "We <br>
agree with this statement, which would supplement basic documents of the <br>
summit, and are sure these principles will enable further work," the <br>
Russian prime minister said. <br>
<p>
The statement laments that efforts of the Minsk Conference co-chairmen <br>
to coordinate the sides' opinions on Karabakh settlement principles were <br>
fruitless. <br>
<p>
The Minsk Conference co-chairmen recommended three settlement principles, <br>
which were supported by all members of the Minsk Group, says the <br>
statement. These are: <br>
<p>
-- territorial integrity of the Azerbaijani Republic and the Republic of <br>
Armenia; <br>
<p>
-- a legal status of Nagorno-Karabakh, outlined in an agreement on the <br>
basis of self-determination, which would give Nagorno-Karabakh the <br>
highest decree of self-government within Azerbaijan; <br>
<p>
-- guaranteed security for Nagorno-Karabakh and its whole population, <br>
including mutual obligations to abide by settlement provisions. (end)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
