<title>Groong Network: WRITING CONTEST: Children's Literature in Armenian</title>
<h1>WRITING CONTEST: Children's Literature in Armenian</h1>
Garbis Armen (<i>bk413@freenet.carleton.ca</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 4 Dec 96 11:57:11 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#22">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#22">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#22">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#22">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0023.html">H.TCHILINGIRIAN@lse.ac.uk: "Armenian Church in Turkey Reopened"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0021.html">KEVORK: "A "KHATCHKAR" IN ATHENS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
OBJECTIVE<br>
To produce boolets of stories, tales and legends, for children aged 6-11,<br>
in the Armenian Language.<br>
<p>
WHO MAY PARTICIPATE<br>
Any person, regardless of nationality or race, who likes to:<br>
       Tell or read stories;<br>
       Has ever dreamt of writing a story or inventing a character;<br>
       Desires to communicate to children, making them laugh and learn;<br>
       Take up a challenge.<br>
<p>
HOW TO PARTICIPATE<br>
Ask for details of this contest - in Armenian, French or English - from:<br>
   <br>
   - KHATOUNE TEMISJIAN,<br>
              Tel: (514) 3 4 3 - 6 6 8 7<br>
              Fax: (514) 3 4 3 - 7 2 8 6<br>
           E-mail: temisjik@ERE.umontreal.ca<br>
<p>
PRIZE<br>
Authors of all the stories accepted by the organizers (see below) <br>
will be awarded prizes and their submission will be published.<br>
<p>
ORGANIZERS<br>
Heritage Language Center, University of Montreal,<br>
Armenian Cultural Circle.      (in colaboration).<br>
<p>
A S K     F O R    D E T A I L S   -   A N D    I N S P I R A T I O N<br>
                                       W I L L    B E    I N F E C T I O U S !<br>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
--
GARBIS  ARMEN        author of:   REBUILD OR RELOCATE?   (US$6.00)
84, Sunnyside        ARMENIA &amp; DIASPORA IN THE 21ST C.    ($12.50)
OTTAWA, ONT.,        AN ARCHITECTURE OF SURVIVAL          ($17.00)
CANADA K1S OR1       I N     A R M E N I A                ($14.00)
</pre>
