<title>Groong Network: A "KHATCHKAR" IN ATHENS</title>
<h1>A "KHATCHKAR" IN ATHENS</h1>
KEVORK (<i>kevork@ath.forthnet.gr</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 4 Dec 96 11:56:36 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#21">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#21">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#21">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#21">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Garbis Armen: "WRITING CONTEST: Children's Literature in Armenian"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0020.html">Embassy of Armenia: "INAUGURATION OF EMBASSY BUILDING IN CANADA"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
    A "KHATCHKAR"-MONUMENT OFFERED BY ARMENIA TO GREECE,"IN GRATITUDE"<br>
<p>
A 3-meter-high monument-a "KHATCHKAR",sculptured in the traditional<br>
armenian form on duff stone,by the armenian artist Sergei Tavitian,<br>
has been erected in the side garden of one of the main avenues of<br>
Athens,Greece.<br>
The monument was offered by the Armenian Red Cross to the people of<br>
Greece,as a gesture of sincere gratitude for the economic and<br>
political support as well as the humanitarian aid extended all<br>
these years to the people of Armenia.<br>
The inauguration took place in the presence of the ambassador of the<br>
Republic of Armenia in Greece Mr. Arman Kiragossian,greek officials<br>
and numerous members of the armenian community in Athens.<br>
The Meyor of Athens,Mr.Dimitris Avramopoulos,before unvailing the<br>
monument,refered to the long lasting traditional bonds,uniting the<br>
armenian and greek people and mentioned that new prospect of cooperation<br>
in various fields are open now for the two countries.<br>
<p>
ATHENS 12-1-1996<br>
<p>
BY KEVORK KOLANIAN<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
