<title>Groong Network: INAUGURATION OF EMBASSY BUILDING IN CANADA</title>
<h1>INAUGURATION OF EMBASSY BUILDING IN CANADA</h1>
Embassy of Armenia (<i>erac@ican.net</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 4 Dec 96 11:40:16 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#20">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#20">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#20">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#20">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0021.html">KEVORK: "A "KHATCHKAR" IN ATHENS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0019.html">Vazgen_Ghoogassian_at_MCMAIL2@ccmail.llumc.edu: "AESA Event"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
ORGANIZING COMMITTEE FOR THE INAUGURATION<br>
OF THE NEW BUILDING OF THE EMBASSY OF ARMENIA <br>
7 Delaware Avenue, Ottawa, Ontario K2P OZ2 <br>
<p>
<p>
P.S.A.<br>
November 15, 1996<br>
For immediate release<br>
<p>
<p>
All Canadian-Armenians are invited to attend the dedication ceremony<br>
of the permanent site of the Embassy of the Republic of Armenia in<br>
Canada. The ceremonies will be held at 2:00 p.m. on Saturday December<br>
7, 1996, at 7 Delaware Avenue in Ottawa. A reception will immediately<br>
follow.<br>
<p>
As you are aware, this year marks the eighth anniversary of the tragic<br>
earthquake of December 7, 1988, in Armenia. Entire villages,<br>
residential and industrial complexes, schools and hospitals were<br>
destroyed. Soviet officials estimated over 25,000 casualties and<br>
500,000 people left homeless. The Armenian Embassy, in collaboration<br>
with the Canadian-Armenian Community, will commemorate the Armenian<br>
Earthquake by hosting special Requiem Prayers on December 6, 1996, in<br>
the House of Commons in Ottawa.<br>
<p>
It is truly symbolic that the inauguration coincides with the<br>
catastrophic earthquake of December 7, 1988, in Armenia. It is,<br>
indeed, testament to the invincible Armenian spirit and will to<br>
flourish in spite of all adversities.<br>
<p>
On this historic occasion, for the first time, Canadian-Armenians from<br>
across the country will witness the blessing and raising of the<br>
tricolour at Armenia's permanent home in Canada. The mission is now<br>
housed in a landmark mansion built with a unique Spanish Revival style<br>
in 1907/8 on the corner of Queen Elizabeth Drive on the Rideau<br>
Canal. It is the third foreign mission to occupy these premises that<br>
have also housed a government agency and several local personalities.<br>
<p>
In the evening of December 7, 1996, the organizing committee has<br>
planned a tribute banquet in honour of the principal donors, Mr. and<br>
Mrs. Sarkis Acopian. The banquet will be held in the Grand Hall of the<br>
Canadian Museum of Civilization at 100 Laurier Avenue in Hall and will<br>
begin at 6:30 p.m. with cocktails. Reservations are required for this<br>
event.<br>
<p>
We look forward to seeing all at these events. Those who are unable to<br>
attend and would like to commemorate this historic occasion with a<br>
contribution can do so by forwarding their gifts to the Embassy of the<br>
Republic of Armenia, 130 Albert Street, Suite 1006, Ottawa, Ontario<br>
K1P 5G4.<br>
<p>
- 30 -<br>
<p>
For more information contact: <br>
Mr. Anto Boghossian	(613) 234-1890 	Ottawa<br>
Mr. Zareh Tchelikjian	(613) 683-8183	Montreal<br>
Mr. Haig Misakyan 	(416) 667-1083	Toronto<br>
Mr. Ashot Grigorian 	(613) 234-3710	Embassy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
