DATE=12/3/96<br>
TYPE=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<br>
NUMBER=2-206970<br>
TITLE=EURO SUMMIT (L ONLY)<br>
BYLINE=KYLE KING<br>
DATELINE=BONN<br>
CONTENT=<br>
VOICED AT: <br>
<p>
INTRO:  OFFICIALS FROM THE 54 MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION FOR <br>
SECURITY AND COOPERATION IN EUROPE ARE ENDING A TWO-DAY MEETING <br>
AIMED AT CHARTING A PATH TOWARD PEACE IN THE 21ST CENTURY.  BUT <br>
AS V-O-A EUROPEAN CORRESPONDENT KYLE KING REPORTS, THE LISBON <br>
GATHERING WAS MARRED BY DEADLOCK OVER KEY SECURITY ISSUES.<br>
<p>
TEXT:  LEADERS AND DIPLOMATS AT THE TWO-DAY SECURITY MEETING HAD <br>
HOPED TO CREATE A WIDE-RANGING PLAN TO BRING, PEACE, DEMOCRACY, <br>
SECURITY, AND HUMAN RIGHTS TO EUROPE IN THE 21ST CENTURY.<br>
<p>
BUT CONTINUED FRICTION ABOUT NATO PLANS FOR AN EASTWARD EXPANSION<br>
OF THE ALLIANCE AS WELL AS A DISPUTE BETWEEN ARMENIA AND <br>
AZERBAIJAN PROVED JUST HOW DIFFICULT SUCH A PATH WILL BE.<br>
<p>
U-S AND EUROPEAN OFFICIALS, WHO SUPPORT NATO PLANS TO TAKE IN NEW<br>
MEMBERS, WERE NOT ABLE TO EASE RUSSIAN FEARS SUCH AN EXPANDED <br>
ALLIANCE WILL THREATEN RUSSIAN SECURITY.<br>
<p>
BELARUS PRESIDENT ALEXANDER LUKASHENKO WAS THE LONE SUPPORTER OF <br>
THE RUSSIAN POSITION.  MR. LUKASHENKO CAME UNDER STRONG CRITICISM<br>
FOR HIS RECORD ON HUMAN RIGHTS.  SOME O-S-C-E MEMBERS CRITICIZED <br>
THE REFERENDUM HE HELD LAST MONTH GIVING HIM SWEEPING NEW POWERS.<br>
<p>
WORK ON THE SUMMIT'S FINAL DECLARATION WAS ALSO HELD UP BY THE <br>
ONGOING DISPUTE ABOUT NAGORNO-KARABAKH, A MOSTLY ARMENIAN ENCLAVE<br>
LOCATED INSIDE AZERBAIJAN.<br>
<p>
BECAUSE ALL O-S-C-E DECISIONS REQUIRE CONSENSUS AMONG THE 54 <br>
MEMBERS, DISPUTES ABOUT SUCH TERRITORIAL ISSUES MAKE BROAD <br>
POLITICAL DECLARATIONS DIFFICULT.<br>
<p>
BUT THE TWO-DAY MEETING WAS NOT WITHOUT SUCCESS.  MONDAY, THERE <br>
WAS AGREEMENT TO HOLD A NEW ROUND OF CONVENTIONAL ARMS TALKS <br>
AIMED AT REDUCING THE NUMBER OF TANKS AND TROOPS IN EUROPE.   <br>
(SIGNED)<br>
<p>
NEB/KBK/JWH/RAE<br>
<p>
03-Dec-96 10:48 AM EST (1548 UTC)<br>
NNNN<br>
<p>
Source: Voice of America<br>
.<br>
