<title>Groong Network: Russian press on the OSCE Lisbon summit</title>
<h1>Russian press on the OSCE Lisbon summit</h1>
Armen Martirossyan (<i>martiros@scf-fs.usc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 3 Dec 96 13:02:59 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#10">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#10">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#10">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#10">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0011.html">Kevork K. Oskanian: "VOA/OSCE Summit"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0009.html">Arthur Martirosyan: "Russian press on the OSCE Lisbon summit"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
        PRESIDENT LEVON TER-PETROSSIAN'S SPEECH IN THE OSCE SUMMIT<br>
        IN LISBON<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 3, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, the OSCE Summit started its works in Lisbon, Portugal. The<br>
 President of the Republic of Armenia Levon Ter-Petrossian, who is<br>
 participating in the Summit, met with the Minister of Foreign Affairs<br>
 of Great Britain Malcolm Rifkind. The sides discussed issues related<br>
 to the Karabagh conflict settlement. On the same day, the Armenian<br>
 President met with the Minister of Foreign Affairs of France Herve de<br>
 Charette.<br>
 During the OSCE Lisbon Summit, the President of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia Levon Ter-Petrossian delievered a speech, in which he said,<br>
 in particular:<br>
 "The main direction of our activities formed immediately after the<br>
 cold war, when the OSCE came forward as a forum with a new vision,<br>
 which allowed to draw to cooperation all the countries left in the<br>
 political vacuum after the dissolution of the block system of<br>
 security. This was achieved also because the OSCE formed itself as a<br>
 "union of universal values" united all its members.<br>
 Armenia highly appreciates its membership in the OSCE.<br>
 The Budapest Summit passed a series of important decision on the<br>
 institutional transformation of the OSCE and the necessity of<br>
 developing a new model of the European security model. Today, we can<br>
 witness an obvious progress in both directions.<br>
 The OSCE made its specific contribution into the vision of the<br>
 problems of security. This vision is not limited to military issues,<br>
 but it considers them in the same context with with humanitarian,<br>
 political, economic and other issues.<br>
 This vision is reflected in our joint efforts for creating a<br>
 universal security system in Europe, as well as in the concrete steps<br>
 for early prevention of conflict, conflict resolution and<br>
 post-conflict rehabilitation.<br>
 An important aspect in guaranteeing security is the improvement,<br>
 passage and implementation of the agreement on ordinary armaments in<br>
 Europe. This process is significantly amplified by the improvement of<br>
 mechanism reflected in the documents of the Forum on Cooperation in<br>
 the Area of Security, which allow for vast field of activities in<br>
 every individual conflict situation.<br>
 The Missions and other specially created structures are efficient.<br>
 The OSCE is present everywhere, where there are conflicts in Europe:<br>
 Bosnia, Chechnya, Nagorny Karabagh, etc.<br>
 In the period after the Budapest Summit, Armenia has taken part<br>
 actively in the activities of the Minsk Group of the OSCE. In<br>
 addition to this process, Armenia became the initiator of direct<br>
 dialogue with Azerbaijan in order to agree on main principles of the<br>
 Karabagh conflict resolution.<br>
 However, I think that in this Summit Azerbaijan is trying to break<br>
 the accepted logics of the negotiation process.<br>
 We strongly believe that if the Karabagh problem is solved based on<br>
 the principles proposed by Azerbaijan, then the people of Karabagh<br>
 will have to live with a constant threat of genocide and forced<br>
 deportation.<br>
 The past experience of the Armenian massacres in Sumgait (February<br>
 1988), Kirovabad (November 1988), and Baku (January 1990),  as well<br>
 as the deportation of the population of 24 Armenian villages in<br>
 Karabagh (May-June 1991) clearly indicates that despite all the<br>
 promises, Azerbaijan is not able to guarantee the security of the<br>
 people of Karabagh.<br>
 That is why we think that the only way to exclude a new tragedy is<br>
 the respect of the right of the people of Nagorny Karabagh to<br>
 self-determination.<br>
 Nevertheless, confirming its commitment to respect the ceasefire,<br>
 Armenia expresses its preparedeness to continue its constructive<br>
 participation in the process of negotiations within the Minsk Group,<br>
 as well as in direct dialogues for the quickest possible resolution<br>
 of the conflict on the basis of a fair compromise.<br>
 In negotiating the present, we should not forget about the future.<br>
 The future security of the region is not possible without wide<br>
 regional coopearation, which will promote the further strengthening<br>
 of mutual trust in security in the process of the peaceful conflict<br>
 resolution.<br>
 As a step in that direction, I could suggest the informal<br>
 consultations between the three Caucasian countries within the<br>
 framework of the OSCE with the participation of other interested<br>
 member countries in order to develop the main directions of the<br>
 regional cooperation, arms control, conflict resolutions, and<br>
 regional integration."<br>
<p>
 P.S. A photo is available:<br>
 03/23 Levon Ter-Petrossian on the Lisbon Summit (Reuter-Armenpress).<br>
<p>
        THE UNITED ARMENIAN FUND SENT $160 MILLION OF AID TO ARMENIA<br>
        IN SEVEN YEARS<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 3, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The United Armenian FUnd completed its seventh year of operations<br>
 with records revenues of $42.4 million during the fiscal year<br>
 1995-1996, according to the audit of its financial statements<br>
 prepared by the accounting firm of Arthur Andersen LLP.<br>
 During this fiscal year, the UAF sent to Armenia by sea and air $40<br>
 million of relief supplies which exceeded the prior year's shipments<br>
 by $10 million, or 33%. The shipments consisted primarily of medical<br>
 supplies. In addition, the UAF funded the Children's Cardiac Center<br>
 of Armenia which to date has performed 693 heart operations.<br>
 During the past seven years, the UAF sent a total of $160 million of<br>
 humanitarian assistance to Armenia on board 87 airlifts and 164 sea<br>
 containers, including $21 million of heating fuel during winter of<br>
 1993-1994.<br>
 The UFA is the collective effort of the Armenian Assemlby of America,<br>
 Armenian General Benevolent Union, Armenian Missionary Association of<br>
 America, Armenian Relief Society, Diocese of the Armenian Church of<br>
 America, Prelacy of the Armenian Apostolic Church of America and<br>
 Lincy Foundation.<br>
<p>
        FADEY SARGISSIAN - "MAN OF THE YEAR"<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 3, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The President of the National Academy of Sciences of the Republic<br>
 of Armenia Fadey Sargissian has been awarded the title of the "Man of<br>
 the Year." Mr. Sargissian will visit the United States to participate<br>
 in the award presentation ceremony.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
