                      Turkish gangster:'We burnt Rhodes'<br>
TURKISH gangster Abdullah Catli,accused by his country's media of carrying<br>
out hit squad killings for Turkey's powerful security apparatus,is also<br>
being held responsible for a series attacks on Greek islands.<br>
An Athens News Agency report from Ankara said the revelation was made<br>
during an interview given to Turkey's HBB TV by goverment MP Sedat Bucak,<br>
head of an anti-Kurdish guerilla militia.Bucak said that among other<br>
"obligations",the late Catli also carried out arson attacks on<br>
Greek islands.<br>
The nationalist Yeni Sefak paper headlined the yesterday,saying,<br>
We burnt Rhodes.<br>
Greek Agriculture Minister Stephanos Tzoumakas said these revelations<br>
only confirmed the long-held belief that overseas powers were also<br>
at work instigating the outbreak of fires on Greek islands.<br>
Bucak and a top policeman were in the same car accident that killed<br>
Catli three weeks ago.<br>
A series of media revelations has ever sinc uncoverd a close relationship<br>
between Catli,once a leading member in the extreme nationalist GREY WOLVES<br>
and a convicted drug smuggler,and Bucak.<br>
     <br>
<p>
     "Arson attacks in Greece among Turkish gangsters' revelations"<br>
  Probe reveals 1988 assassination in Athens and arson on Greek islands<br>
<p>
TURKEY'S opposition leader Mesut Yilmaz accused the Islamist-led goverment<br>
yesterday of attempting to cover up a scandal over Turkey's alleged in<br>
ATHENS of Agop Agopian,a member of Armenia's anti-Turkish armed groop,<br>
Asala.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
ATHENS NEWS  11-28-1996<br>
<p>
<p>
FROM:KEVORK KOLANIAN<br>
