<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI - 19DEC96 - RUSSIA UPSET OVER ADAMS/KHACHUKAEV MEETING</title>
<h1>OMRI - 19DEC96 - RUSSIA UPSET OVER ADAMS/KHACHUKAEV MEETING</h1>
<i>fsu@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 30 Dec 96 16:41:19 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#59">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#59">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#59">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#59">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0060.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "Interfax 30Dec96 Azeri President Favors CIS Cooperation"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0058.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI - 19DEC96 - RUSSIA UPSET OVER ADAMS/KHACHUKAEV MEETING"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     PRESIDENT ALIYEV: AZERBAIJAN FAVORS EFFECTIVE CIS COOPERATION<br>
     <br>
     BAKU,  Dec  30  (Interfax)  -  Azerbaijan  attaches  much<br>
     significance to  its  participation  in  the  Commonwealth  of <br>
     Independent States and favors effective cooperation within the<br>
     CIS, President  Heydar Aliyev  said at a meeting with Russia's <br>
     Ambassador to Azerbaijan Alexander Blokhin in Baku today.<br>
     Aliyev said  he wished  the  CIS  would  achieve  further<br>
     integration among its members economically and socially.<br>
     On Russian-Azerbaijani  relations, the president recalled<br>
     that this  year the  two countries had managed to deepen their <br>
     cooperation, although "a lot of untapped potential remains."<br>
     Azerbaijan and  Russia  have  noticeably  improved  their<br>
     cooperation  in  a  bid  to  settle  the  Armenian-Azerbaijani <br>
     conflict, Aliyev said.<br>
        That was  "clearly demonstrated"  during the  preparation<br>
     for the  OSCE summit  in Lisbon  earlier this month and during the <br>
     summit  itself, he  said. Aliyev thanked the Russian side, including  <br>
     Prime  Minister  Viktor  Chernomyrdin  and  Foreign Minister Yevgeny <br>
     Primakov, for their support at the summit.<br>
     The Azerbaijani  president also voiced the hope that 1997<br>
     would become "crucial" in terms of efforts toward settling the <br>
     Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict.  "Not a  single day  should  be wasted. <br>
     This question must be resolved in 1997," the president stressed.<br>
     Blokhin presented  Aliyev with  a  message  from  Russian<br>
     President Boris  Yeltsin, offering his Azerbaijani counterpart best <br>
     wishes  for the  New Year  and inviting him to attend the CIS summit <br>
     in Moscow next month.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
