<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI - 5DEC96 - HELSINKI WATCH PROTESTS TO ALIEV</title>
<h1>OMRI - 5DEC96 - HELSINKI WATCH PROTESTS TO ALIEV</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 05 Dec 96 14:24:57 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#50">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#50">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#50">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#50">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0051.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 6DEC96 - MEDIA CRACKDOWN IN AZERBAIJAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0049.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 3DEC96 - ARMENIAN, AZERBAIJANI PRESIDENTS CLASH AT OS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     HELSINKI WATCH PROTESTS TO ALIEV. The Helsinki Watch human rights <br>
     organization has sent a letter to President Heydar Aliev protesting <br>
     the handling by the Azerbaijani authorities of the criminal case <br>
     against former Defense Minister Rahim Ghaziev, Turan reported on 4 <br>
     December. The letter said that Gaziev was repeatedly not allowed to <br>
     meet with his relatives or his lawyer, who so far has only had one <br>
     meeting with his client. Gaziev was Azerbaijan's defense minister in <br>
     the government of former President Abulfaz Elchibey, and fled to <br>
     Russia after Aliev came to power in June 1993. Gaziev was charged with <br>
     the "surrender" of the Shusha and Lachin towns to Armenian forces in <br>
     May 1992 and sentenced to death in absentia. He was extradited by <br>
     Russia in April 1996 at Azerbaijan's request. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0051.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 6DEC96 - MEDIA CRACKDOWN IN AZERBAIJAN"</a>
