<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI - 21Nov96 - Azerbaijani Foreign Minister on Nagorno-Kar</title>
<h1>OMRI - 21Nov96 - Azerbaijani Foreign Minister on Nagorno-Kar</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 21 Nov 96 11:37:56 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#45">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#45">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#45">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#45">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0046.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "Interfax -- 24 November, Nagorno-Karabakh elections decried"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0044.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 20Nov96 - Protests Over Beating of Azerbaijani Journa"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     AZERBAIJANI FOREIGN MINISTER ON NAGORNO-KARABAKH PEACE TALKS. <br>
     Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Hasan Hasanov has refuted Armenian <br>
     presidential spokesman Levon Zurabyan's statement that Azerbaijan <br>
     refused to participate in drafting a declaration of principles on a <br>
     settlement to the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict (see OMRI Daily Digest, 20 <br>
     November 1996), Turan reported on 20 November. Hasanov said a draft <br>
     declaration proposed by the Armenian side contradicts the "interests <br>
     of Azerbaijan," because it does not respect his country's territorial  <br>
     integrity. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
