<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI - 15Nov96 - Berezovskii Visits Tbilisi and Baku</title>
<h1>OMRI - 15Nov96 - Berezovskii Visits Tbilisi and Baku</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 15 Nov 96 11:05:53 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#42">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#42">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#42">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#42">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 19Nov96 - Clinton Praises Azerbaijan's Stance on CFE"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 15Nov96 - U.S. Delegation Visits Baku"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     BEREZOVSKII VISITS TBILISI . . . Russian Deputy Security Council <br>
     Secretary Boris Berezovskii, on his second visit to Georgia in less <br>
     than a week, met for two hours behind closed doors with Georgian <br>
     President Eduard Shevardnadze on 14 November to discuss the situation <br>
     in Abkhazia, Chechnya, and the North Caucasus in general, Russian <br>
     media reported. -- Liz Fuller<br>
     <br>
     . . . AND BAKU. Berezovskii then flew to Baku where he discussed <br>
     Russian-Azerbaijani relations, the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, and the <br>
     situation in Chechnya with Azerbaijani President Heidar Aliev, noting <br>
     that the "urgent" problems of the region are linked and should be <br>
     tackled jointly. Berezovskii also tried to persuade Aliev of the <br>
     advantages of exporting Azerbaijan's Caspian Sea oil via the <br>
     "northern" pipeline that runs through Dagestan and Chechnya, according <br>
     to Turan. Aliev told TRT on 14 November, however, that he would prefer <br>
     that Azerbaijan's "strategic" (as opposed to "early") oil be exported <br>
     through the proposed Baku-Ceyhan pipeline, but that unnamed members of <br>
     the consortium engaged in exploiting the deposits in question oppose <br>
     that option. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 19Nov96 - Clinton Praises Azerbaijan's Stance on CFE"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 15Nov96 - U.S. Delegation Visits Baku"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
