<!-- body="start" -->
     U.S. DELEGATION VISITS BAKU. A U.S. government delegation headed by <br>
     James Collins, special advisor to the U.S. secretary of state on the <br>
     newly independent states, and the U.S. special envoy to the OSCE Minsk <br>
     Group, Joseph Presel, held talks in Baku on 13 November with <br>
     Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Hasan Hasanov and President Heidar Aliev, <br>
     ITAR-TASS reported. Collins expressed concern that the disputed status <br>
     of the Caspian Sea could jeopardize several major oil consortiums; <br>
     Hasanov assured him that Azerbaijan's laws "guarantee the safety of <br>
     foreign companies." Collins handed Aliev a message from U.S. President <br>
     Bill Clinton expressing hope that a document on conditions for <br>
     resolving the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict will be signed during the <br>
     December OSCE heads of state summit in Lisbon. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
