<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI - 12Nov96 - Azerbaijan's Oil Output Falls</title>
<h1>OMRI - 12Nov96 - Azerbaijan's Oil Output Falls</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 12 Nov 96 10:26:40 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#39">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#39">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#39">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#39">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0040.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "CENASIAN  BATTALIN  MAY  BACK  KARABAKH PEACEKEEPING  EFFORT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0038.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 12Nov96 - Caspian Sea Agreement Signed"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     AZERBAIJAN'S OIL OUTPUT FALLS. Azerbaijan's oil output has declined <br>
     for the fifth consecutive year, from 15 million metric tons in 1991 to <br>
     an estimated 9 million tons for 1996, according to Nezavisimaya gazeta <br>
     on 11 November. The decline is the result of a lack of investment and <br>
     the loss of Azerbaijan's traditional export markets. The IMF <br>
     delegation that visited Baku in August made the disbursement of a <br>
     further $300 million loan contingent on the raising of domestic oil <br>
     prices. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0040.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "CENASIAN  BATTALIN  MAY  BACK  KARABAKH PEACEKEEPING  EFFORT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0038.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 12Nov96 - Caspian Sea Agreement Signed"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
