<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI-- 21 Oct 1996-- LUKOIL ON NEW CONTRACT WITH AZERBAIJAN</title>
<h1>OMRI-- 21 Oct 1996-- LUKOIL ON NEW CONTRACT WITH AZERBAIJAN</h1>
<i>arichter@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 21 Oct 96 12:06:58 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#29">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#29">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#29">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#29">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0030.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--22 Oct 1996--LEADERS OF TURKIC-SPEAKING COUNTRIES MEET"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0028.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--16 Oct 1996--NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 LUKOIL DISCUSSES NEW CONTRACT WITH AZERBAIJAN.  The president and vice <br>
 president of LUKoil held talks in Baku on 19 October with Azerbaijan's state <br>
 oil company SOCAR and President Heidar Aliev on the joint exploitation of the <br>
 Inam off-shore Caspian deposit, which has known reserves of 120-150 million <br>
 metric tons, Turan and ITAR-TASS reported. LUKoil wants a 50% share in the <br>
 project. Speaking at a press conference in Baku on 19 October, Aliev mentioned <br>
 as additional spheres for cooperation with LUKoil the creation of a joint <br>
 insurance company and of a company for the overhaul of floating oil rigs. -- <br>
 Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0030.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--22 Oct 1996--LEADERS OF TURKIC-SPEAKING COUNTRIES MEET"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0028.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--16 Oct 1996--NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
