<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--16 Oct 1996--NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED</title>
<h1>OMRI--16 Oct 1996--NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 16 Oct 96 11:43:12 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#28">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#28">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#28">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#28">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0029.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "OMRI-- 21 Oct 1996-- LUKOIL ON NEW CONTRACT WITH AZERBAIJAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0027.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--Oct 14 1996--FRENCH FOREIGN MINISTER IN BAKU"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
     <br>
     <br>
     NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED. Representatives of the British <br>
     company Ramco, Mobil, and Total have formed a consortium to carry out <br>
     exploratory work in the southern Caspian Sea, Turan reported on 15 <br>
     October. Representatives of the three constituent companies have held <br>
     talks in Baku with Azerbaijani President Heidar Aliev and the head of <br>
     Azerbaijan's state oil company SOCAR. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
