<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--Oct 14 1996--FRENCH FOREIGN MINISTER IN BAKU</title>
<h1>OMRI--Oct 14 1996--FRENCH FOREIGN MINISTER IN BAKU</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 14 Oct 96 16:15:51 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#27">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#27">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#27">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#27">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0028.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--16 Oct 1996--NEW AZERBAIJANI OIL CONSORTIUM CREATED"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0026.html">kkhalmatov@sorosny.org: "OMRI--10 OCT 1996--AIOC CHAIRMAN NAMES DATE FOR EXPORT OF FI"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
     FRENCH FOREIGN MINISTER IN BAKU. During a one-day visit to Baku on 11 <br>
     October, French Foreign Minister Herve de Charette met with <br>
     Azerbaijani President Heidar Aliev and Foreign Minister Hasan Hasanov, <br>
     Turan and ITAR-TASS reported. The talks focused on France's <br>
     participation in the Nagorno-Karabakh mediation process, the prospects <br>
     for French participation in the exploitation of Azerbaijan's Caspian <br>
     Sea oil deposits, Aliev's scheduled January visit to France, and <br>
     French support for Azerbaijan's cooperation with the EU and the <br>
     Council of Europe. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
