<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--20 September 96--ARMENIAN PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION UPDATE</title>
<h1>OMRI--20 September 96--ARMENIAN PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION UPDATE</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 20 Sep 96 15:45:39 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#17">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#17">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#17">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#17">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0018.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--26 September 96--AZERIS DISTURBED BY JOINT RUSSIAN-ARM"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0016.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--18 September 96--BADALYAN'S CAMPAIGN PROGRAM"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     ARMENIAN PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION UPDATE. According to a poll published <br>
     on 19 September in Express-Khronika, 57.3% of respondents said they <br>
     will vote in the 22 September presidential election for united <br>
     opposition candidate Vazgen Manukyan. Incumbent President Levon <br>
     Ter-Petrossyan would take 33.7% of the vote, Communist Party candidate <br>
     Sergei Badalyan 8.2%, and Scientific-Industrial Civic Union leader <br>
     Ashot Manucharyan 0.7%. Ter-Petrossyan 's campaign fund had raised 168 <br>
     million drams ($ 410,450) by 17 September, according to a <br>
     representative of the fund, Noyan Tapan reported on 18 September. Some <br>
     44 million drams ($107,500) have already been spent. -- Elin <br>
     Suleymanov<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
