<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--17 September 97--BOTAS GETS WORLD BANK LOAN FOR BAKU-C</title>
<h1>OMRI--17 September 97--BOTAS GETS WORLD BANK LOAN FOR BAKU-C</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 17 Sep 96 15:12:49 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#14">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#14">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#14">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#14">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0015.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--17 September 96--NAZARBAYEV IN BAKU"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0013.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--COUNCIL OF CIS BORDER FORCES MEETS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     BOTAS GETS WORLD BANK LOAN FOR BAKU-CEYHAN STUDY. The World Bank on 12 <br>
     September announced in a news release it will loan $5 million to <br>
     Turkey's oil and gas transmission company Botas to undertake a <br>
     feasibility study and environmental audit of several route options for <br>
     exporting up to 45 million metric tons of crude oil per year from <br>
     Azerbaijan and Central Asia. It appears routing options beginning in <br>
     Baku and transiting Armenia or Georgia to Ceyhan will be evaluated. <br>
     According to the news release, World Bank assistance for the study <br>
     does not imply a commitment to further finance the pipeline as it is <br>
     expected to be built and financed by the private sector. -- Lowell <br>
     Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0015.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--17 September 96--NAZARBAYEV IN BAKU"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0013.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--COUNCIL OF CIS BORDER FORCES MEETS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
