     IRAN DEMANDS EXTRADITION. Iran has demanded the extradition of Piruz <br>
     Dilenji, chairman of the South Azerbaijan National Liberation <br>
     Committee (SANCL), and a number of other Iranian emigrants living in <br>
     Azerbaijan, Segodnya reported on 4 September. Iran has been pressuring <br>
     Azerbaijan to back up its declared neutrality towards the nationalist <br>
     movement in Azeri-populated northern Iran with concrete steps. <br>
     Dilenji, who said Azerbaijani officials have warned him that he may be <br>
     extradited to Iran, may have to choose between leaving Azerbaijan and <br>
     halting his activities. -- Elin Suleymanov<br>
