<!-- body="start" -->
     MUTALIBOV SUPPORTERS SENTENCED. The Supreme Court of Azerbaijan has <br>
     sentenced Adyl Gadzhiev, a close associate of former Azerbaijani <br>
     President Ayaz Mutalibov, and Kenan Gyurel, an Austrian citizen of <br>
     Turkish origin, to 14- and 15-year prison sentences for taking part in <br>
     the alleged March 1995 coup attempt, as a result of which at least 50 <br>
     people were killed, ITAR-TASS reported on 6 September. President <br>
     Heidar Aliev has often accused Mutalibov, who fled to Moscow in 1992, <br>
     of trying to assassinate him. -- Elin Suleymanov<br>
