<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--28 August 96--AZERBAIJAN'S FOREIGN MINISTER IN TEHRAN</title>
<h1>OMRI--28 August 96--AZERBAIJAN'S FOREIGN MINISTER IN TEHRAN</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 28 Aug 96 11:53:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#4">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#4">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#4">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#4">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0005.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--28 August 96--AZERBAIJAN CREATES ANTI-NARCOTICS COMMIS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0003.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     AZERBAIJAN'S FOREIGN MINISTER IN TEHRAN. Hasan Hasanov, in Tehran on a <br>
     two-day official visit, assured President Ali Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani <br>
     on 27 August that Azerbaijan wishes to improve its relations with <br>
     Iran, which have been clouded by the recent arrests of Azerbaijani <br>
     religious activists accused of links with Iranian intelligence, <br>
     Reuters reported. Hasanov also met with his Iranian counterpart, Ali <br>
     Akbar Velayati, and discussed an upcoming meeting of foreign ministers <br>
     of Caspian littoral states which is to propose a new ruling on the <br>
     division of the Caspian. Iranian parliament speaker Ali Akbar <br>
     Nateq-Nuri expressed his anger at negative Azerbaijani media coverage <br>
     of Iran, according to AFP, quoting IRNA. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
