<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Azerbaijan: OMRI--13 August--AZERBAIJANI COUP-PLOTTERS ARRESTED</title>
<h1>OMRI--13 August--AZERBAIJANI COUP-PLOTTERS ARRESTED</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 13 Aug 96 11:23:32 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#1">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#1">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#1">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#1">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0002.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--15 August 96--AZERBAIJANI STATE OIL COMPANY REASSURES"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0000.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "OMRI - "Wanted" Azerbaijanis Hiding in Turkey - Aug 10, 1996"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     AZERBAIJANI COUP-PLOTTERS ARRESTED IN DAGESTAN. Three men wanted in <br>
     Azerbaijan in connection with the March 1995 coup-attempt were <br>
     arrested in a joint Russian-Azerbaijani operation in Dagestan, <br>
     according to an 8 August Interfax report monitored by the BBC. -- <br>
     Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
