<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: War isn't declared, but...</title>
<h1>War isn't declared, but...</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 16:43:39 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#1">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#1">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#1">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#1">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0002.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Deaths of political prisoners in Azerbaijan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0000.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "List of ill political prisoners"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
 <br>
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                 <br>
   E-mail RELCOM: eldar@ipca.baku.az, eldar@hrcenter.baku.az    <br>
 3-11,28th May St.,Baku 370014,Azerbaijan;tel/fax (8922)987555  <br>
                     = May 30, 1995 =                           <br>
<br>
     <br>
     Decree of National Assembly of  AR  #367  on  November  4'92 <br>
     "About interpretation of concept 'in fighting conditions' in <br>
     Crime Code of Azerbaijanian Republic"<br>
     <br>
     With purpose of providing a single understanding of concept<br>
'in fighting  conditions'  mentioned in articles of Crime Code of <br>
Azerbaijanian Republic" in the chapter on military crimes and  in <br>
connection of   the  operations  are  directed  to  violation  of <br>
souvereignity and territorial unity  of  Azerbaijanian  Republic, <br>
National Assembly of Azerbaijanian Republic decrees:<br>
     1. To explain that 'fighting conditions'  mentioned  in  the<br>
articles of  Crime  Code of Azerbaijanian Republic in the chapter <br>
on military crimes are meant the  situation  of  military  units, <br>
standing immediately  in  opposition  to  enemy in both front and <br>
rear, and also of military units providing  the  fighting  tasks, <br>
even in the rear.<br>
     2. To charge the Minister of  Defense  of  AR,  Minister  of<br>
Internal Affairs  of  AR,  Minister  of  National Security of AR, <br>
Chairman of Committee for the protection of state boarder  of  AR <br>
to provide  the  declaration  of  this  decree  to  personnel and <br>
explaining work together the Court Collegium on Military Cases of <br>
Supreme Court  of Azerbaijanian Republic,  military tribunals and <br>
military procurator.<br>
     <br>
     I.Qambarov,<br>
     Chairman of Supreme Soviet of Azerbaijanian Republic<br>
     <br>
     Baku, November 4'92<br>
------------------------<br>
     <br>
     Decree of  National  Assembly  of  AR #747 on November 26'93 <br>
     "About  interpretation  of  concept  'in  other  aggravating <br>
     circumstances' mentioned in Articles 73 and 74 of Crime Code <br>
     of Azerbaijanian Republic"<br>
     <br>
     With purpose  of  providing a single understanding and right<br>
using of concept 'in other aggravating  circumstances'  mentioned <br>
in  Articles  73,  prt  2  and  74,  part  2  of  Crime  Code  of <br>
Azerbaijanian  Republic,  National  Assembly   of   Azerbaijanian <br>
Republic decrees:<br>
     1. To  explain,  that  the  concept  'in  other  aggravating<br>
circumstances' mentioned in Articles 73,  prt 2 and 74, part 2 of <br>
Crime Code of Azerbaijanian Republic must be meant also the  time <br>
of fighting operations for the liberation of Nagorno-Karabakh and <br>
other territories of Azerbaijanian Republic.<br>
     2. This decree is valid till to special decree.<br>
     3. To  charge  the  Supreme  Court of AR,  Procurator of AR,<br>
Ministry of Justice of AR and Ministry of Defense  of  AR<br>
to provide  the  explanation  of  this  decree  to population and <br>
draftees.<br>
     <br>
     R.Quliyev,<br>
     Chairman of Supreme Soviet of Azerbaijanian Republic<br>
     <br>
     Baku, November 26'93<br>
     <br>
     <br>
     <br>
