<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Deaths of political prisoners in Azerbaijan</title>
<h1>Deaths of political prisoners in Azerbaijan</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 16:55:18 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#2">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#2">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#2">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#2">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0003.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Political persecutions in Azerbaijan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0001.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "War isn't declared, but..."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
 <br>
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                 <br>
        3-11, 28th May Street, 370014 Baku, Azerbaijan          <br>
        Tel +994-12-947550, fax +994-12-942471/987555           <br>
           E-mail InterNet: eldar@hrcenter.baku.az              <br>
                      = December 15, 1995 =                     <br>
<br>
     <br>
           DEATHS OF POLITICAL PRISONERS IN AZERBAIJAN <br>
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
                         Doubtful deaths<br>
                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The special  anxiety  of  Azerbaijan  opposition  and  human<br>
rights  activists  is  about  the  cases  of  doubtful  deaths of <br>
prisoners arrested on the political  accusations.  Excluding  few <br>
Armenian terrorists died in Bayilov prison in 1992, there was not <br>
registered other deaths of political prisoners before the  Heydar <br>
Aliyev's return to power in June 1993.<br>
     On July  16'93  in  Bayilov prison (SIZO-1) in Baku died the<br>
former commander of  Agdam  volunteers'  batallion  of  "Karabakh <br>
Falcons"  YAQUB  RZAYEV,  called also as Qatir Mammed (the famous <br>
rebel of Tsar period) for the personal courage.  He died  4  days <br>
before  the  trial,  in  the  day  when the Parliament passed the <br>
resolution about new investigation of surrender of  Khojali  town <br>
in Nagorno-Karabakh  to  Armenian  armed  forces.  Rzayev who was <br>
arrested in the time of Popular Front's government in  late  1992 <br>
on  the  charge of banditry could reportedly be important witness <br>
of this event  and  also  was  well  informed  about  the  hidden <br>
activity of PFA in Agdam region. Since the Parliamentary hearings <br>
on July 15-16'93 began the arrests of opposition  leaders  [1,2]. <br>
According  unofficial sources,  Rzayev was tortured,  but doctors <br>
reported about the infarct of heart.<br>
     In Autumn 1993,  in same Bayilov prison died ARMEN AVANESIAN<br>
and ARNO MKRTCHIAN,  the ethnic Armenians who were  sentenced  to <br>
death for  terrorism.  According official information,  the first <br>
one died because of pleurisy and total  intoxication  and  second <br>
one from chronic tuberculosis [3].  However, the died people were <br>
not visited by ICRC and their corpses were not given to Armenians.<br>
     On May  15'94,  in  the same prison died also NATIQ QURBANOV<br>
arrested for the illegal custody of weapon.  He was in the past a <br>
bodyguard  of  former Minister of Defense Rahim Qaziyev sentenced <br>
to the death for the military and political crimes. His death was <br>
officially confirmed only during the trial started in August 1994 <br>
[4,5].  Unofficial sources reported that his corpse  looked  very <br>
exhaust.<br>
     On February 6'95, the activist of Qubadli regional branch of<br>
Popular Front NOVRUZ NOVRUZOV died  during  the  trial.  As  some <br>
other members of illegal military unit of "Qaranqush" established <br>
by PFA,  he was accused of killing several officials in  Qubadli. <br>
The death was caused by the heart attack.  It liked true, because <br>
his brother Guloglan Novruzov died for the same cause in  January <br>
1994  after he had seen on TV the accusation speach of Procurator <br>
General against the PFA activists [6].<br>
     On June 29'95,  in the hospital of Shuvelyan Prison (SIZO-3)<br>
died MP,   former  commander  of  frontier  guard  in  Nakhchivan <br>
Autonomous Republic,  activist of opposition Party  of  "Musavat" <br>
SHAHMARDAN (Shahsultan) MAHAMMAD OGLU JAFAROV. He was searched by <br>
the police since August 28'94 and arrested on June 17'95 in Julfa <br>
region. During the  arrest  he  was  wounded  by  5  bullets  and <br>
transported  to  the  Nakhchivan  Central Hospital [7,8].  It was <br>
happened 17 days later the Praliament sanctioned his  arrest  [9] <br>
and 5 days before the trial over 19 his supporters [10]. Although <br>
he  needed  the  quiet  after  2  medical  operations,   he   was <br>
transported  from  Nakhchivan  to Baku.  Reportedly,  he had been <br>
detained there 3 days without the adequate treatment [11].  Group <br>
of  opposition  deputies  of  Parliament  and international human <br>
rights organizations demanded the investigation  which  not  been <br>
made.<br>
     On July  10'95,  the  Chairman  of  Charitable  Society   of<br>
"Nidjat" NUSRET  QASIM  OGLU BUDAGOV died in Investigation Prison <br>
of Ministry of National Security.  He was extradicted from Russia <br>
in late May 1995 as one of the main organisers of attempt of coup <br>
d'etat in Ganja city on October 4'94 ("October case"). It was the <br>
first  extradiction  since Azerbaijan Parliament has initialed in <br>
March 1995 the treaty with Russia  on  mutual  legal  assistance. <br>
There  were  the rumors about the tortures over Budaqov,  but his <br>
relatives did not demand any investigation  [12].  Probably,  the <br>
reason  of that is that they are afraid for the fate of Budaqov's <br>
son Namiq who was also arrested on this case and sentenced to the <br>
long-term imprisonment.<br>
     On November  19'95,  in  the  Baku  prison  died  MP  SEYFAL<br>
BABAYEV. He  was  arrested  by sanction of Parliament on November <br>
5'95 for the organization of killing the H.Aliyev's supporter  in <br>
May 1990  [13].  It was well-known that his health was bad and he <br>
was repeatedly treatened without any hopeness [14].<br>
     On November 25'95, in the Prison Hospital in Boyuk Shor died<br>
the Vice-Chairman   of   Social-democratic   Party,   teacher  of <br>
Agricultural Academy  AYPARA  NASREDDIN OGLU ALIYEV.  The healthy <br>
36-years old man was arrested on October  7'94  on  the  "October <br>
case."  Soon,  his liver became ill. Immediately before the trial <br>
his health had worsened,  and  on  October  22'95  he  fell  into <br>
comatose situation and was transported from Bayilov Prison to the <br>
Boyuk Shor Hospital,  where he died one month later  without  the <br>
adequate  medical  treatment.  The corpse was burried without any <br>
serious investigation [15].<br>
     On December 5'95,  in the Correcting  Work  Colony  (ITK-12)<br>
probably died  the  activist  of PFA,  member of illegal military <br>
unit "Qaranqush" NATIQ AHMEDOV (see case  of  Novruzov).  He  was <br>
sentenced in  February  1995  to  the  13-years  imprisonment for <br>
killings.<br>
     <br>
                Probable attempts upon the lives<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The opposition  sources  report often about the tortures and<br>
other ill-treatment in Azerbaijan prisons.  There are  only  some <br>
cases of immediate danger for the lives of political prisoners.<br>
     So, according the statement  of  arrested  Vice-Chairman  of<br>
PFA, former commander of Lachin regiment Arif Pashayev,  on April <br>
16'94 was happened the attempt to poison him in the Investigation <br>
Prison of   Ministry   of   National  Security  (SIZO  MNB).  The <br>
investigator gave him the cup of tea, and his state was worsened. <br>
After  the  necessary  treatment  was officially stated about the <br>
"dietetic gastritis" [16].<br>
     On July 12'94,  in  the  same  prison  was  the  attempt  of<br>
poisoning the  former  Vice-Minister  of Defense Alakram Hummatov <br>
who was arrested for the separatism.<br>
     On September 22'94,  above mentioned persons together former<br>
Minister of  Defense  Rahim  Qaziyev  and  his former deputy Baba <br>
Nazarli were kidnapped from SIZO MNB.  According latest statement <br>
of A.Pashayev, the Assistant Chief of Investigation Department of <br>
MNS Faiq Mirzoyev was instructed to kill them for the "attempt of <br>
escape," but  instead  that  freed  them and escaped together the <br>
prisoners. Nazarli died later in Moscow  hospital  with  doubtful <br>
circumstances, Qaziyev  hides in Russia,  and other were arrested <br>
again [17].<br>
     <br>
                     Position of authorities<br>
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The government  of  Azerbaijan  is still denied the facts of<br>
ill-treatment in the detention centers. However,<br>
- the fair investigation does not make even in the cases of deaths<br>
  of arrested members of Parliament;<br>
- ICRC delegate has not an access to the prisoners accused/sentensed<br>
  on the political accusations;<br>
- both  local  and  foreign  human  rights activists have not the<br>
  right of visiting the political prisoners;<br>
- the  appeals  of  international human rights organizations like<br>
  Amnesty International or Human Rights Watch are ignored.<br>
     All of them make the official statements unconvincing.<br>
     <br>
     Eldar Zeynalov,<br>
     Director.<br>
     <br>
                             Sources<br>
                             ~~~~~~~<br>
