<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: General information about HRCA</title>
<h1>General information about HRCA</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 16:54:06 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#4">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#4">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#4">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#4">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0005.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Desertion and draft evasion in Azerbaijan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0003.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Political persecutions in Azerbaijan"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
 <br>
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                 <br>
    150-9, Bashir Safaroglu Street, 370000 Baku, Azerbaijan     <br>
 Tel+994-12-947550, fax 942471, e-mail: eldar@hrcenter.baku.az  <br>
<br>
     <br>
              THE HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN <br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The Human  Rights  Center  of  Azerbaijan is non-registered,<br>
non-governmental, non-political,  non-profit organization created <br>
on May  1993  by  free journalist and human rights activist Eldar <br>
Zeynalov. The  main  purposes  of that were the disagreement with <br>
the  political  censorship  in  Azerbaijan,  which  blocked   the <br>
publications  about  the  human rights violations in the country, <br>
and the necessity of the constant information on the human rights <br>
situation  for  local  and global human rights organizations like <br>
Amnesty International, Human Rights Watch, Moscow Helsinki Group, <br>
Helsinki Citizens' Assembly etc.<br>
     The main  form  of the work of HRCA is the monitoring of the<br>
human rights situation with the publication  of  the  information <br>
bulletin, thematic   reports,   lists  of  prisoners  etc.  Other <br>
direction of its work is the re-printing the human rights reports <br>
of other  organization  with  translation to the local languages. <br>
HRCA propagates also  the  electronic  mail  in  the  information <br>
exchange in the human rights field.  It provides some local NGO's <br>
by the e-mail link with Western colleagues.<br>
     The programs carrying out by HRCA, are:<br>
- monitoring  the human rights situation in Azerbaijan (supported<br>
  by microgrants of different persons and NGOs);<br>
- monitoring  the  forced  migration  in Azerbaijan (supported by<br>
  Open Society Institute);<br>
- free  translation  office  for  local  e-mail  network  of NGOs<br>
  (supported by International Olof Palme Center).<br>
     For the present  HRCA  has  the  small  staff,  including  6<br>
people.<br>
     <br>
     Eldar Zeynalov,<br>
     Director of HRCA<br>
     <br>
     <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
