<!-- received="Thu Aug 15 16:38:29 1996 EST" -->
<!-- sent="Thu, 15 Aug 96 16:56:18 EST" -->
<!-- name="agalietti@sorosny.org" -->
<!-- email="agalietti@sorosny.org" -->
<!-- subject="Desertion and draft evasion in Azerbaijan" -->
<!-- id="9607158401.AA840152895@mail.sorosny.org" -->
<!-- inreplyto="" -->
<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Desertion and draft evasion in Azerbaijan</title>
<h1>Desertion and draft evasion in Azerbaijan</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 16:56:18 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#5">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#5">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#5">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#5">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0006.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Tofiq Qasimov (3)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0004.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "General information about HRCA"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                 <br>
            E-mail RELCOM: eldar@hrcenter.baku.az               <br>
 3-11,28th May St.,Baku 370014,Azerbaijan;tel/fax (8922)987555  <br>
                      = June 08, 1995 =                         <br>
<br>
     <br>
          THE DESERTION AND DRAFT EVASION IN AZERBAIJAN <br>
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
The Azerbaijani  Republic  is  being  in  the  situation  of  the <br>
undeclared war  with  neighbour  Armenia  since  1988,  when  the <br>
Armenian  Parliament  claimed  the  joining  of  Nagorno-Karabakh <br>
Autonomous District to Armenian Republic.  In the  Soviet  period <br>
(before end  of  1991)  Azerbaijan  had  not  own  army  and  the <br>
policemen and volunteers fighted in the battles.  The articles of <br>
the  Crime  Code on deserting and draft evasion were related only <br>
with the Soviet Army.<br>
     <br>
When the independence of the republic was claimed,  on the Autumn <br>
1991 was established the National Army of Azerbaijan (NAA). After <br>
the collapse the USSR were handed over the NAA all weapon and the <br>
part  of  the personnel of former 4th Army (ethnical Azeris).  In <br>
the same time were began also the call-up and the  responsibility <br>
for the military crimes, including deserting and draft evasion.<br>
     <br>
The main   rules   in   this   area   were   Decrees  "About  the <br>
recruitment of the Armed Forces of Azerbaijan"  on  February  19, <br>
1992,  and  "About  the adjournment from the call-up" on November <br>
14,  1992.  They established the privileges for the only sons  in <br>
the families, fathers of 2 and more children, students.<br>
     <br>
The possibility  of the alternative military service was declared <br>
in 1991 and is  confirmed  by  every  call-up's  decree  [1,2,3]. <br>
Reportedly,  the  unpublished law "About the alternative military <br>
service of Azerbaijan Republic" mentioned only religious  reasons <br>
for  the  enrolment  to  this  service.  As  said the Head of the <br>
Department  of  Defense  Ministry,   Chinqiz   Mammedov,   mainly <br>
Christians  of  the Baptist and Adventist Churches have the right <br>
to alternative  service.  The  pacifism  as  the  reason  is  not <br>
mentioned [4].<br>
     <br>
In principle,   the   possible  order  for  the  call-up  to  the <br>
alternative service must be follows:  the citizen  gives  to  the <br>
District  Military Commissariat the application and the reference <br>
from his Church,  after that the question will be decided by  the <br>
Republican  Military Commissariat [4].  However,  as informed the <br>
Deputy for the  law  affairs  of  Military  Commissioner  of  the <br>
Azerbaijan  Republic  Agajavad  Javadov,  "now is not the certain <br>
procedure of the call-up to the alternative service,  and in  the <br>
meanwhile  nobody  from the Azerbaijan citizens was not called up <br>
to it" [5].<br>
     <br>
On the May  12,  1994  was  established  the  cease-fire  on  the <br>
Azeri-Armenian  front.  Now  here are not the military operation, <br>
but the call-ups are continuing.  For example, they were declared <br>
by the decree of the President on Juny 22,  1994 [4],  August 25, <br>
1994 [2].  By  the  anonimous  information  from  the  Republican <br>
Military  Commissariat,  in  the  begin of 1995 will be called up <br>
14,000 men [6].  Moreover,  by the Decree on June 22,  1994  were <br>
liquided  the  privileges,  which  was mentioned in the mentioned <br>
Decrees on February 19, 1992 and November 14, 1992 [2].<br>
     <br>
So, for the present only three group of the men have the right of <br>
the  adjournment.  These  are the men have 4 and more children at <br>
their maintenance; the students and post-graduate students of the <br>
Day Departments of the Universities and Institutes;  the men, who <br>
have at their maintenance the invalids  of  1st  and  2nd  groups <br>
(grades)  [2].<br>
     <br>
The statistics of the desertion and draft evasion is closed,  but <br>
its scale may be characterized by the follows.  For  the  present <br>
call-up  age for rankers is from 18 to 35 years,  and for reserve <br>
officers is to 45 years.  During the Soviet period every  call-up <br>
gave  the  Soviet Army about 50,000 rankers.  The regular call-up <br>
could give the NAA about 900,000 fighters. If the NAA is equal to <br>
the Armenian forces included about 30-50 thousands soldiers, then <br>
draft evasion spreads all over 90 percent of the men  of  call-up <br>
age.<br>
     <br>
The officers  of  the  Military Commissions recognize themselves, <br>
that the call-up and mobilization are not  taking  their  regular <br>
course.  "The  half  men older than 19 years are deserters," said <br>
the Military Commissioner of the Sabayil District  of  Baku  City <br>
Mehman  Mansurov  [7].  In  his  speech  on April 17,  1994,  the <br>
President said about the arrears of the men called up,  which was <br>
about 30%, and about desertiong the whole batallions [8].<br>
     <br>
The main ways of draft evasion are as follows:<br>
     <br>
a. Liberation by the bribes<br>
     <br>
It is very expensive way,  because the price of the liberation is <br>
about some thousands USD.  It is used mainly by the rich sections <br>
of the  population like salesmen or relatives of the officials of <br>
low and middle level.<br>
     <br>
On February 9,  1994 the Parliament discussed  the  case  of  the <br>
Military Comissioner of Qaradag District M.Jafarov,  who assisted <br>
to the illegal liberation  of  145  men  from  the  call-up  [9]. <br>
Sometimes  the  information  about same cases is published as the <br>
separate and rare [10],  but the true scale of this  abusing  the <br>
power is more large.  On April 1994 were retired from their posts <br>
and sent to the front 3 Military Commissioners [8].  As  informed <br>
the  Military  Commissioner of Azerbaijan,  colonel Asif Abbasov, <br>
after the prime-minister S.Huseynov was retired on October  1994, <br>
in  the  Commissariat  were  demobilized 20 officers,  demoted 11 <br>
officers and changed 6 District Commissioners [11].<br>
     <br>
b. Liberation by the connections<br>
     <br>
This way is  accessible  only  for  the  relatives  of  the  high <br>
officials. For  example,  the call-up aged son of Samur Novruzov, <br>
the Chair of the Foreign Tourism Council was sent to USA for  the <br>
study, and  the  necessary  sum  (17,500  USD)  was paid from the <br>
budget of the Agricultural Ministry [12].<br>
c. Enter the universities<br>
     <br>
In Azerbaijan are dozens of University, Institutes and other high <br>
schools.  Early  entering  to them to liberate automatically from <br>
the call-up,  but in 1994 they were reregistrated and the  almost <br>
of  the private high schools did not get the sertification.  Some <br>
students were detained by military police and  sent  to  the  NAA <br>
[13].  Reportedly,  the  group  of the workers of High Navigation <br>
School in Baku was arrested by getting the  bribe  for  enter  in <br>
this high school [10].<br>
     <br>
d. Emigration from Azerbaijan.<br>
     <br>
It is the main way.  The young men, who have not enough money for <br>
the liberation,  emigrated to the neighbour republics of ex-USSR, <br>
mainly Russia.  Generally their migration is not  registrated  in <br>
Azerbaijan,  because  it  is  forbidden  by  the  law,  but it is <br>
possible to buy a permit to leave the country for  the  bribe  in <br>
300  USD.  They  do  not  change  their citizenship,  because the <br>
Azerbaijanian citizenship protects them from the call-up  to  the <br>
local armies.  The Russian-Azerbaijanian treaty on the mutual aid <br>
in the crime cases was initialed by the National Assembly  (Milli <br>
Mejlis) of  Azerbaijan  only  on  March  9,  1995 [14].  The same <br>
agreement is also  between  the  Procurators  of  Azerbaijan  and <br>
Ukraine since May 17, 1994 [15]. There were no cases to hand over <br>
the deserters,  but it is  possible  by  the  conditions  of  the <br>
agreements.<br>
     <br>
In the Crime Code of Azerbaijanian Republic are a few articles on <br>
the  punishment  on  deserting  and draft evasion.  These are the <br>
absense without leave (Art.240  and  241),  deserting  (Art.242), <br>
escape from  military  unit during the fighting (Art.243),  draft <br>
evasion (Art.73), evasion from the mobilization (Art.74) and from <br>
military  service  by  self-mutilation  or other modes (Art.244), <br>
which are punished even in the peace time.  Before the peace pact <br>
between  Azerbaijan  and  Armenia  the situation is considered as <br>
'war' with all results [16].<br>
     <br>
In this case returning deserter may be punished to: <br>
- 5-10 years (Art.73)<br>
- 5-15 years or death (Art.74),<br>
- 2-10 years (Art.240),<br>
- 5-10 years (Art.241),<br>
- 5-10 years or death (Art.242),<br>
- 5-15 years or death (Art.243),<br>
- 5-10 years or death (Art.244).<br>
     <br>
The first  case  of  arrests  for the desertion was registered on <br>
January  1992  (during  so-called  "Dashalti   operation").   The <br>
occupation  by  the  Armenians 11 Districts of Azerbaijan (7 from <br>
them are without disputed Nagorno-Karabakh) started  some  trials <br>
on some military crimes, including deserting [17].<br>
     <br>
Now these  cases  are  the  common phenomenon in Azerbaijan.  For <br>
example,  only in Sabunchi District of Baku were investigated 107 <br>
cases  of  the  deserters,  and some cases were finished to July, <br>
1994 [18].  During two weeks after the Decree on August  9,  1994 <br>
were arrested about 500 deserters [19]. The police arrested about <br>
492 former criminals,  which were amnested and sent to the  front <br>
and then deserted [20].<br>
     <br>
Generally, the  sentences and other statistics on these cases are <br>
not published. In the known cases the sentences were rough: 10-15 <br>
years  of  prisonment  [21],  15 years [22].  There is the common <br>
tendention to make the punishment more  cruel.  So,  in  1993  in <br>
Azerbaijan  were  sentenced to death 22 people,  in 1994 - 23 (in <br>
2.3 times more than in Russia with its 150-millions  population). <br>
By  the  opinion  of  the  Member of the Collegium of the Justice <br>
Ministry,  Chairman of the Lawyers Union,  Dr. Ilham Rahimov, the <br>
situation is related with the activity of Military Tribunal [23]. <br>
It is the probable reason of  these  statistics  are  hidden.  In <br>
fact,  in  1993  was  published  the  information  about 12 death <br>
sentences [24].  Only one from them was about the sentence of the <br>
Military  Tribunal,  which was already abolished by the President <br>
[21].  Dr.Rahimov  considers,  that  in  1994   were   also   the <br>
executions.<br>
     <br>
The President  as  the  final  instance  for  the  appeal did not <br>
generally mitigate  a  punishment  to  the  deserters  and  draft <br>
evaders.  Only  once  he  amnested the group of 44 deserters from <br>
NAA,  which were arrested for the  deserting  in  December  1993, <br>
during  the  Armenian  attack in the Beylaqan District.  One from <br>
this group was sentenced to the death,  13 men to the 10-15 years <br>
of  prison,  the  25  cases were in the Military Tribunal,  and 5 <br>
soldiers were under the investigation [21].<br>
     <br>
In the whole,  the cease-fire changed nothing. No the battues for <br>
the forcible recruitment,  which were often in the near past [25, <br>
26,13] and used sometimes for political [27] and  moral  pressure <br>
[28].  However  now  is  the confusion with the evaluation of the <br>
present situation.  It was one of  the  topics  of  special  wide <br>
conference  of  the  Military Tribunals and Military Collegium of <br>
the Supreme Court on February 1995,  where was recommended to use <br>
more  regular  the  Article 42 of the Crime Code [29].  According <br>
this article, the criminal military serviceman can be sent in the <br>
war period to the front with the respite of punishment.<br>
     <br>
The typical  example  of  usual practice is the case Sardar Eldar <br>
oglu Alibalayev,  born 1973 [30].  It was  a  draft  evader  from <br>
December 1993 to September 1994.  Then he realized his guilty and <br>
came to the District Military Commissariat,  where  was  forgived <br>
and sent to the reception unit.  However the police arrested him, <br>
and he was sentenced by the District People Court to 7  years  of <br>
prisonment  for  the draft evasion (Art.73,  part 2).  During the <br>
sitting of the trial the Procurator considered as the aggravating <br>
fact,  that Alibalayev return after ending of the operations,  in <br>
the "peaceful time".  He demanded to use part 2 of  the  article, <br>
which  was  made  more rough by the National Assembly on November <br>
26, 1993 [31] (already  after  the  crime!)  and  using  for  the <br>
punishment  in the "war time".  But he refused to use the Art.42, <br>
because "the time is peaceful" and there are not the operations.<br>
     <br>
This undefinity makes possible the violation of the principles of <br>
humanity  and  justice.  The  protests  of the political [27] and <br>
civic [32] organizations  are  ignored  by  the  government,  and <br>
spontaneous civic movement is forcible suppressed [13,26,33].  In <br>
these conditions the deserters,  draft evaders,  who have  not  a <br>
money  for  the  bribe,  also pacifists,  conscentious objectors, <br>
political oppositioners can be punished disproportionally severe.<br>
     <br>
     Eldar Zeynalov,<br>
     Director<br>
     Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan<br>
     <br>
     <br>
