<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Extradition of Azeri political emigrants</title>
<h1>Extradition of Azeri political emigrants</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 17:01:11 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#8">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#8">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#8">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#8">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0009.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Statistics on IDP"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0007.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Tofiq Qasimov (2)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
EXTERNAL                                   AI Index: EUR 04/03/96<br>
<p>
                                                    17 April 1996<br>
<p>
Further information (1) UA 101/96 (EUR 04/02/96, 15 April 1996)<br>
- Fear of Forcible Repatriation / Fear for Safety / Death penalty<br>
<p>
RUSSIA/AZERBAIJAN        Rahim Hasan oglu QAZIYEV and<br>
                         Ayaz MUTALIBOV<br>
<p>
Amnesty International has learned with great  regret  that  Rahim<br>
Qaziyev, detained in Moscow on 14 April, was forcibly repatriated<br>
to Azerbaijan on 16 April 1996.  Amnesty International fears that<br>
he  will  suffer  serious  human rights violations in Azerbaijan,<br>
specifically torture, ill-treatment and the death penalty.<br>
<p>
Rahim Qaziyev's wife was unable to obtain access to  the  central<br>
police  station  Petrovka  38  in  Moscow where he was reportedly<br>
still  detained  in  the   afternoon   of   16   April.   Amnesty<br>
International  does  not  know  what  procedures,  if  any,  were<br>
available  to  Rahim  Qaziyev  to  appeal  against  his  forcible<br>
repatriation.<br>
<p>
Amnesty International   is   now   calling   on  the  Azerbaijani<br>
authorities to guarantee the  safety  of  Rahim  Qaziyev  and  to<br>
ensure that he is not subjected to torture or ill-treatment.  The<br>
organization is also appealing to the President of Azerbaijan  to<br>
commute Rahim Qaziyev's death sentence.<br>
<p>
Former President  Ayaz  Mutalibov,  detained  on  11  April,   is<br>
reportedly  held  in  the medical ward of the detention centre of<br>
the Moscow  City  Directorate  of  Internal  Affairs  (GUVD)after<br>
suffering  heart  problems.  The Office of the Russian Prosecutor<br>
General stated on 16 April that a decision  as  to  the  forcible<br>
repatriation of Ayaz Mutalibov had not yet been taken.<br>
<p>
FURTHER RECOMMENDED ACTION:<br>
Please send  telegrams/faxes/express/airmail  letters in Russian,<br>
English or in your own language:<br>
<p>
To the Russian authorities:<br>
- expressing  regret  at  the   Russian   authorities'   forcible<br>
repatriation  of  Rahim  Qaziyev  despite  fears that the he will<br>
suffer serious human rights violations in Azerbaijan;<br>
- urging  the Russian authorities not to extradite Ayaz Mutalibov<br>
to Azerbaijan;<br>
- reminding  the  Russian  authorities of their obligations under<br>
international law,  in particular under  the  Convention  against<br>
Torture<br>
<p>
To the Azerbaijani authorities:<br>
- urging  the  Azerbaijani authorities to guarantee the safety of<br>
Rahim Qaziyev and ensure that he is not subjected to  torture  or<br>
ill-treatment in detention;<br>
- urging the President of Azerbaijan to grant clemency  to  Rahim<br>
Qaziyev and commute his death sentence.<br>
<p>
APPEALS TO:<br>
<p>
