<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 AZERBAIJAN NATIONAL COMMITTEE OF HELSINKI CITIZENS' ASSEMBLY   <br>
  Phone +994-12-933378, fax 987555, e-mail hca@ngonet.baku.az   <br>
         3-11, 28th May, Baku 370014, Azerbaijan / CIS          <br>
<br>
     <br>
        INFORMATION ABOUT DISPLACED PERSONS IN AZERBAIJAN <br>
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
According informations on April 1,  1995,  the numbers of  DP  in <br>
Republic  were  149542 families or 667.866 people.  Among them in <br>
cities are 403168 people or 69,37% and in countrysides are 264698 <br>
people or 39,37%.<br>
     <br>
In the regions closely the front settled following numbers of DP:<br>
     Agdam       region    8,085 families, 33,065 people <br>
     Beylaqan              5,474           22,528<br>
     Barda                15,103           66,778 <br>
     Qazax                 1,605            5,990 <br>
     Imishli               6,521           36,682 <br>
     Qedabey                  97              352 <br>
     Goranboy              1,096            5,027 <br>
     Terter                5,026           21,701 <br>
     Tovuz                   323            1,804 <br>
     Total:               42,804          202,969<br>
     <br>
DP settled in Lankaran zone:<br>
     Lankaran region         185 families     801 people <br>
     Lerik                     8               23 Masalli <br>
                     207              836 Calilabad       <br>
             474            2,183 Bilasuvar             <br>
     5,774           28,400 Yardimli                 16   <br>
                 62<br>
     Astara                   25              119 <br>
     Total:                6,689           30,424<br>
     <br>
Quba-Qusar zone:<br>
     Quba region             109 families,    475 people <br>
     Qusar                     5               16 <br>
     Divichi                 122              464<br>
     Xizi                    142              722 <br>
     Sayazan                  69              264 <br>
     Xachmaz                 134              602 <br>
     Total:                  630            2,781<br>
     <br>
                      Nationalities of DP<br>
     <br>
     Azeris are 659,732 people,<br>
     Kurds        7,754<br>
     Russians       317<br>
     Turks           54<br>
     <br>
Numbers of DP by sex: male are 291,235, famale are 357,562. Among <br>
them 120,617   young   men,  140,109  young  women.  From  86,383 <br>
pensioners male are 39,422, female are 47,941.<br>
     <br>
                         Employable DP:<br>
     <br>
In Republic their number are 319,752  people  (142,267  are  men, <br>
177,484 women),   including  settled  in  industrial  cities  and <br>
provided by jobs:<br>
     <br>
 Places               Employable           Provided by job<br>
                Total      Men    Women    Total    Men    Women<br>
On Republic     319,752  142,207 177,484  93,804  50,184  43,620 <br>
Baku             85,376   34,956  50,420  24,561  10,842  13,719 <br>
Ali-Bayramli      2,448    1,137   1,311     592     344     246 <br>
Qanca             5,198    2,034    3,164  3,055   1,492   1,563 <br>
Minqechevir       7,780    3,570    4,210  2,903   1,560   1,343 <br>
Sumqayit         26,432   12,112   14,320  6,502   5,226   1,276<br>
     <br>
     <br>
               Profession (with industrial cities):<br>
     <br>
                   1        2        3       4      5      6<br>
     <br>
On Republic   130,386   18,188    9,856   13,204  42,661  105,457 <br>
Baku           45,306    8,135    4,629    4,189  13,437   10,834 <br>
Ali-Bayramli      367       85        7      147     254    1,039 <br>
Minqechevir       511      576      244      189     977    7,923 <br>
Qanca             212      331      132      125     244    4,154 <br>
Sumqayit       10,632    1,756    1,200    2,095   6,937    3,895<br>
     <br>
     1 - agricultural workers,<br>
     2 - teachers,<br>
     3 - public health employers,<br>
     4 - builders,<br>
     5 - other professions,<br>
     6 - without professions.<br>
     <br>
Accordingly, as result of the wrong settlement of DP,  the places <br>
of their  temporary  living are mainly the industrial cities.  In <br>
Baku agricultural workers are 44,826 from 86,376 DP,  in Sumqayit <br>
are 10,628 from 26,432, and naturelly they are forced to work not <br>
for their professions.<br>
     <br>
                            Education<br>
     <br>
The educations of DP on April 1 in Republic are:<br>
     high education                          43,737 people <br>
     incomplete high and secondary special   47,737 <br>
     secondary                              184,361 <br>
     incomplete secondary                   116,204<br>
including Baku<br>
     high education                          18,034 people <br>
     incomplete high and secondary special   19,744 <br>
     secondary                               60,482 <br>
     incomplete secondary                    17,698.<br>
     <br>
                          Financial aid<br>
     <br>
Each family  of DP is registrated by the local Regional Executive <br>
Authority. According  law  "About  refugees  and  DP", they   are <br>
provided by  job,  privileges  and get humanitarian aid from both <br>
state structures  and  charitable  organizations.  According  the <br>
decree of  President  from November 15,  1994,  each member of DP <br>
family gets the aid in  the  rate  of  minimal  salary  (for  the <br>
present 5,500   Manat),   every   child  gets  3,000  Manat,  and <br>
poverty-stricken families use also other state privileges.<br>
     <br>
In the same time,  the DP families  in  near  front  regions  and <br>
places of  compact  living  are  provided by the humanitarian aid <br>
under the control of international charitable organizations.<br>
     <br>
In the Republic 143,506 DP are supported  by  state,  cooperative <br>
and private rent structures,  160,157 live account of pension and <br>
aid, 29,656 on the account only pension, 139,298 are supported by <br>
private persons and organizations, 195,249 have other sources.<br>
     <br>
Avaz Hasanov,<br>
     <br>
Chairman of Commission for Refugees<br>
of Azerbaijan National Committee of HCA.<br>
     <br>
