<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Tofiq Qasimov's case</title>
<h1>Tofiq Qasimov's case</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 17:00:17 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#12">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#12">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#12">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#12">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0013.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Forced migration in Azerbaijan in 1995"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0011.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Refugees and IDP in Azerbaijan"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
                                                News Service 33/96<br>
AI INDEX: EUR 55/06/96<br>
21 FEBRUARY 1996<br>
     <br>
AZERBAIJAN - AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL URGES THE AUTHORITIES TO ENSURE <br>
APPROPRIATE MEDICAL TREATMENT FOR IMPRISONED POLITICAL OPPONENT<br>
     <br>
The Azerbaijani  authorities should ensure that Tofiq Qasimov,  a <br>
possible prisoner of conscience, receives all appropriate medical <br>
treatment  following  his  transfer  from prison to hospital last <br>
week, Amnesty International said today.<br>
     "At least two prisoners in ill-health are  alleged  to  have<br>
died  as  a  result  of  inadequate medical treatment in the past <br>
year.  We are concerned that Tofiq Qasimov may also suffer  as  a <br>
result of inadequate medical care," the human rights organization <br>
said.<br>
     Tofiq Qasimov, under arrest since September 1995, is said to<br>
have  been  diagnosed  in  recent days as suffering from reactive <br>
psychosis,  a  serious   mental   health   problem   induced   by <br>
environmental circumstances.  On 16 February,  he was transferred <br>
from an investigation prison of the Ministry of National Security <br>
to a prison hospital.<br>
     Amnesty International  is  seeking  further information from<br>
the Azerbaijani authorities on Tofiq  Qasimov's  reported  mental <br>
state  as  well as his treatment,  prognosis and plans for future <br>
care.  According to the United Nations Standard Minimum Rules for <br>
the  Treatment  of  Prisoners,  any prisoner requiring specialist <br>
medical care  should  be  transferred  to  a  specialist  medical <br>
facility to obtain such treatment.<br>
     Tofiq Qasimov,   a   member   of  parliament  and  prominent<br>
political figure in Azerbaijan,  has been charged with complicity <br>
in a failed coup attempt in March 1995.  Amnesty International is <br>
concerned about allegations that the charges are false,  and have <br>
been  fabricated  in  order  to  punish  Tofiq  Qasimov  for  his <br>
non-violent political activity in opposition to  the  Azerbaijani <br>
Government.  The  organization  is also concerned that he faces a <br>
possible death sentence if convicted.<br>
     In a report issued in January (Azerbaijan -  Allegations  of<br>
ill-treatment  in  detention,  AI Index:  EUR 55/01/96),  Amnesty <br>
International expressed its  concern  at  continuing  allegations <br>
that   detainees   have   been  ill-treated  by  law  enforcement <br>
officials.<br>
     <br>
     <br>
