<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Death penalty in Azerbaijan (old)</title>
<h1>Death penalty in Azerbaijan (old)</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 17:30:00 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#15">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#15">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#15">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#15">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0016.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Comments to the US State Dept country report 1995"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0014.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Contacts for HR Campaining"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                   <br>
 150-9, Bashir Safaroglu Street, 370000 Baku, Azerbaijan     <br>
Tel+994-12-947550, fax 987555, e-mail: eldar@hrcenter.baku.az     <br>
                 = March 12, 1996 =                        <br>
     <br>
              DEATH PENALTY IN AZERBAIJAN REPUBLIC <br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
                           Background<br>
                           ~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Azerbaijani Republic  became an independent state in May 28,<br>
1918. Soon,  the death  penalty  was  accepted  as  an  exclusive <br>
punishment. It  was  abolished  in  January  1920 and restored in <br>
1922. In the period from 1947  to  1950  the  death  penalty  was <br>
changed to 25-years imprisonment [1].<br>
     Since 1950 the death penalty is used for the wide  range  of<br>
crimes. Acting  list  of  crimes which are punishing by the death <br>
was adopted in 1958 and includes 34 articles of Crime Code. Among <br>
them are:<br>
     - military crimes                            - 16 articles; <br>
     - specially dangerous state crimes           - 6;<br>
     - other state crimes                         - 6; <br>
     - crimes against a person                    - 2; <br>
     - crimes against a state property            - 1; <br>
     - malfeasance                                - 1; <br>
     - crimes against the order of administration - 1; <br>
     - crimes against the social security and<br>
       social order                               - 2.<br>
     The military   crimes  are  usually  judged  by  the  closed<br>
sessions of Military Tribunals or Military Collegium  of  Supreme <br>
Court. It  is  the reason what the big part of death sentences is <br>
not published.<br>
     The death  penalty is not used if the criminal have been not<br>
full age in the moment of crime [2].  This punishment  for  women <br>
was abolished on October 21'94 [3].<br>
     It is important to note that since 1992 the death  sentences<br>
are  being  passed  by  the  court of so-called "Nagorno-Karabakh <br>
Republic" in the territory controlled by  ethnic  Armenians.  For <br>
example,  the  Ukrainian  mercenary  served in the Azerbaijan Air <br>
Forces Yury Belichenko was sentenced on May 23'94 to  death  [4], <br>
which was later reportedly abolished [5].<br>
     <br>
            Conditions of imprisonment and executions <br>
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     According to Art.22 of Crime Code,  the mode of execution is<br>
the shooting.  The executioner shoots to the occiput of prisoner. <br>
In the  execution  take  part  also  Chief of prison,  doctor and <br>
priest [6].<br>
     The prisoners sentenced to death are detained in only prison<br>
of Azerbaijan. It is so-called "Bayilov Prison," which is used as <br>
the  investigation  prison  (SIZO-1) and the place of serving the <br>
imprisonment.  This prison is accounted as safely and  till  1994 <br>
was known only case of escape (future dictator of USSR I.Stalin). <br>
But on October 1'94 the group of sentenceds to death  escaped  by <br>
undermining [7].  To day practically all of them (9 from 10) were <br>
rearrested or killed [8].<br>
     There are   not   a  long-time  the  information  about  the<br>
executions.  Since 1993,  in Azerbaijan were not  the  executions <br>
[9].  The Chief of the Sector on the mercy problem of Presidental <br>
Executive Staff Irada Hasanzade confirmed that during 1995  there <br>
had been not executions [10].<br>
     For that reason the Bayilov prison is overcrowded. According<br>
to the above-mentioned advocate T.Ismiyev,  some prisoners waited <br>
the execution  4-5  years.  Instead  the one-man cells,  they are <br>
detained in those cells by 5-6 people.  More than 10 people  died <br>
already by the natural death [11].<br>
     <br>
                           Statistics<br>
                           ~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Reportedly, Azerbaijan is  the  country  with  traditionally<br>
high rate of death penalties. So, the President of Lawyers' Union <br>
of Azerbaijan, Director of Reserch Institute of Problems of Legal <br>
Examination,  Criminalistics and Criminology,  Dr.  Ilham Rahimov <br>
stated that during  two  last  "Soviet"  decades  (1971-1991)  in <br>
Azerbaijan were  sentenced  to  death  more  than 400 people [6], <br>
i.e., the average rate of such sentences is about 20 yearly.<br>
     It is  confirmed  by  the Chief of Department of Research of<br>
Legal Experience,  Rafael  Gvaladze,  and  Department  Consultant <br>
Ilyas  Mammedov,  who  said  that  the  average  figure  of death <br>
sentences in  Azerbaijan  since  1991  are  18-20   yearly   [1]. <br>
Dr.I.Rahimov  informed  about 22 sentenced in 1993,  and 23 death <br>
sentences in 1994 [6]. Only Baku City Court sentenced to death 25 <br>
people in 1991-1994 [12].<br>
     The official figure of the sentenceds to  death  in  1989-95<br>
are  73  people,  among  them 66 for the killing with aggravating <br>
circumstances, 4 for banditry, 2 for diversion and 1 for the high <br>
treason  [9].  But  the independent expert,  member of Advocates' <br>
Collegium since 1955,  Dr.  Teymur Ismiyev estimated in September <br>
1995 the total figure of sentenced as about 100 people [11].<br>
     <br>
                     Death penalties in 1995<br>
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     As it was above mentioned, the half articles related with<br>
the death  penalty  are  the  military crimes.  Because of closed <br>
sessions of them and existing military censorship,  this part  of <br>
death sentences is hidden from the mass media.<br>
     From the open sources are known 15 cases of 1995.<br>
     Victor Alexandrovich Osminkin,  DOB 1958,  was sentenced  to<br>
the death by Baku City Court on February 17'95 [13].<br>
     In early April two killers, Sahib Quliyev and Nazim Zeynalov<br>
were sentenced to death for the serial killings  by  the  Supreme <br>
Court [14].<br>
     On April 11'95, the resident of Goychay city, Elshan Ibrahim<br>
oglu Ibrahimov,  DOB  1975,  was  sentenced  to the death for the <br>
double killing by the Supreme Court as court  of  first  instance <br>
[15].<br>
     On April  26'95,  Baku  City  Court sentenced to death Mayil<br>
Mirismayil oglu Muradov, DOB 1970 [13].<br>
     In early  May  1995 four activists of illegal armed group of<br>
"Qaranqush" established by the Qubadli branch  of  Popular  Front <br>
were  sentenced  to  death  for  the killing of some officials in <br>
Qaranqush  region  during  the  Armenian  attack,  robbery,   and <br>
stealing the  weapon.  The  names  of  the sentenceds are Intiqam <br>
Qayibov, Sahib Mammedov,  Yashar Shahmuradov, Rovshan Asadov. The <br>
sentence was passed by the Collegium of Supreme Court [16].<br>
     On May 13'95,  the former Minister of Defense Rahim  Qaziyev<br>
was sentenced  to  death  for  the surrender of Shusha and Lachin <br>
regions to Armenians [17].  He  escaped  from  the  Investigation <br>
Prison of Ministry of National Security on September 22'94 [18].<br>
     In early  August  1995,  the  ethnic  Armenian,  citizen  of<br>
Russia, Kamo   Saakov   was   sentenced  to  the  death  for  the <br>
preparation of diversion, illegal custody of weapon and explosion <br>
materials, and contraband [19].<br>
     On August 10'95,  the Supreme Court sentenced to  the  death<br>
Ismayil Ibad oglu Baxshaliyev, DOB 1972 [13].<br>
     Supreme Court sentenced to  death  on  October  3'95  Mammed<br>
Hasan oglu Mustafayev, DOB 1927 [13].<br>
     On October 26'95,  the Military Collegium of  Supreme  Court<br>
sentenced  to  death the resident of Ganja city,  former Chief of <br>
City Military Police Eldar Aliyev.  He was accused in the attempt <br>
of  coup  d'etat  of  October  4'94  and  sentenced  for the high <br>
treason, establishment of illegal armed group, etc. [20].<br>
     On October  27'95,  Agalar  Hadjimirza  oglu  Mehmanov   was<br>
dentenced to the death by the Supreme Court [13].<br>
     Five from above-mentioned people were amnested in 1995. They<br>
are:   I.Baxshaliyev,   A.Mehmanov,   M.Muradov,    M.Mustafayev, <br>
V.Osminkin.<br>
     <br>
                   Perspectives of abolishment<br>
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Since 1993, when the death penalties were stopped, there was<br>
published an information about 5 people amnested in 1993 (Russian <br>
mercenaries) [21], 1 person amnested in 1994 (deserter) [22], and <br>
7 criminals amnested in 1995 [13].<br>
     The high  level  of  crimes  urges the public to support the<br>
necessity of death penalty.  So,  in  January  1995  the  opinion <br>
polling in Baku showed that 82.4% respondents are for it [23]. In <br>
May 1995 was published the results of  other  polling  given  81% <br>
supporters  of  capital  punishment  [6].  In  January 1996,  the <br>
official press informed about 83.6%  population  supporting  this <br>
measure  [9].  Therefore  the  abolishment  of  death  penalty in <br>
Azerbaijan likes for the near future as impossible.<br>
     In December 1995,  the President changed for  7  people  the<br>
death penalty to 16 and 20-years  term  of  imprisonment  [9,13]. <br>
That  punishments are not in the acting Crime Code,  but they are <br>
discussed as the alternate punishment.  This  action  may  be  an <br>
examination of public opinion.<br>
     <br>
                 Death sentences are continuing<br>
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     On January 26'96,  the death sentence to  former  member  of<br>
Special Police  Unit  J.Qadimov  for  the  attempt of coup d'etat <br>
began the  list  of sentenced in 1996 [24].  On February 12,  two <br>
more death sentences were passed to former Minister  of  National <br>
Security Nariman  Imranov  and former Deputy Minister of Defense, <br>
Talish nationalist leader Alakram  Hummatov.  All  of  them  were <br>
punished for the political crimes.<br>
     <br>
                             Sources<br>
                             ~~~~~~~<br>
 1. "Press-Fakt", 1 December 1995<br>
 2. Art.22 of Crime Code of Azerbaijan Republic <br>
 3. "Millet", 26 October 1994<br>
 4. "Noyan Tapan" Agency, 24 May 1994 <br>
 5. "Gunay", 12 November 1994<br>
 6. "Zerkalo", 6 May 1995<br>
 7. "Azadliq", 4 October 1995<br>
