15. "7 Gun", 29 April 1995<br>
16. "Gunay", "Azadliq", 4 May 1995<br>
17. "Azadliq", 13 May 1995<br>
18. "ANS-press", 23 September 1994; "Gunay", 24 September 1994 <br>
19. "7 Gun", 5 August 1995<br>
20. "Press-Fakt", 15 December 1995; "Azadliq", 16 December 1995 <br>
21. "Azerbaycan", 4 August 1993; "Vyshka", 25 September 1993 <br>
22. Azerbaijan TV, 3 January 1994<br>
23. "Molodezh Azerbaidzhana", 31 January 1995 <br>
24. "Azerbaycan", 30 January 1996<br>
     <br>
                List of crimes punishing by death<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
57   - "Treason of mother-land"<br>
57-1 - "Using the legal armed forces against Azerbaijan people<br>
       and constitutional institutions"<br>
58   - "Espionage"<br>
59, p.1 - "Terrorist act"<br>
60, p.1 - "Terrorist act against representative of forein state" <br>
61   - "Diversion"<br>
70   - "Banditry"<br>
70-1 - "Actions desorganising the work of corrective working<br>
       institutions"<br>
70-2 - "Establishment of illegal armed groups" <br>
74, p.2 - "Evasion from the mobilisation"<br>
80, p.2 - "Manufacture or sale of false money or securities" <br>
81, p.2 - "Violation of regulations about currency operations" <br>
88-1 - "Embezzlement of state or public funds in the special<br>
       big volume"<br>
94   - "Premediated murder with aggravating circumstances" <br>
109, p.3 - "Rape"<br>
170, p.2 - "Bribing"<br>
191-1- "Attempt to the life of policemen"<br>
212-2- "Driving away or seizure of train,  aircraft, sea or river<br>
        ship, also  seizure  a station,  airdrome,  port or other <br>
        transport enterprise,  institution,  organization, also a <br>
        seizure the cargos without the goal of stealing.<br>
233  - "Insubordination" {to commander during the operations} <br>
235"v" - "Resistance to the commander  or  forcing  him  for  the<br>
       violence of duties"<br>
237"b" - "Violent actions to the commander" <br>
242"b","g" - "Desertion"<br>
243  - "Unauthorized escape from  the  military  unit  during the<br>
       operations"<br>
244"b" - "Evasion from the military service by self-mutilation or<br>
       other way"<br>
246"v" - "Premeditated destruction or damage of military property" <br>
250"e" - "Violation of guard service regulations"<br>
252"g" - "Violation of the battle duty regulations"<br>
255"v" - "Abuse  of  the  power,  exceeding  the  authority  and<br>
         negligent attitude to the (military) service"<br>
256 - "Handing  over  or  abandonment of the means of war to the<br>
      enemy"<br>
257"b" - "Leaving the sinking military ship"<br>
258 - "Unauthorized escaping the battlefield or  refusal  to  use<br>
      the weapon"<br>
259 - "Voluntary surrender to captivity" <br>
261 - "Pillage" (marauding)<br>
262 - "Violation over the population in the operations' region"<br>
     <br>
Note: After the date of issuing this report, the Azerbaijan <br>
Parliament adopted in June the amendments to the Crime Code, and <br>
reportedly, the number of such articles was decreased. But before <br>
the official publication we can't update this list.<br>
     <br>
