<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Comments to the US State Dept country report 1995</title>
<h1>Comments to the US State Dept country report 1995</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 15 Aug 96 17:43:48 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#16">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#16">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#16">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#16">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0017.html">Anthony Galietti: "Review of Political Arrests and Trials in Azerbaijan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0015.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Death penalty in Azerbaijan (old)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
<p>
<p>
                            COMMENTS<br>
              to the US State Dept's country report<br>
               on human rights - Azerbaijan, 1995<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;One opposition  politician  died  while in  jail,  while  others </i><br>
<i>&gt;complained of receiving poor medical care.</i><br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Section 1</i><br>
<i>&gt;A.Political and other extrajudicial killing</i><br>
     <br>
In 1995, at least 6 political prisoners died  in jails and prisons:<br>
     <br>
* February 6'95 - the activist of Qubadli regional branch of<br>
  Popular Front Novruz Novruzov died<br>
     <br>
* June  29'95  -  in the hospital of Shuvelyan jail (SIZO-3) died<br>
  MP, former commander of frontier guard in Nakhchivan Autonomous <br>
  Republic,  activist of opposition Party of "Musavat" Shahmardan <br>
  (Shahsultan) Jafarov.  During the arrest he was  wounded  by  5 <br>
  bullets.<br>
     <br>
* July 10'95 - the Chairman of Charitable  Society  of  "Nidjat",<br>
  one of the leaders of unsuccessful coup attempt of October 1994 <br>
  Nusret Budaqov died in  Investigation  Prison  of  Ministry  of <br>
  National Security.  He  was  extradited from Russia in late May <br>
  1995.<br>
     <br>
* November 19'95 - in the Baku ("Bayilov) prison died  MP  Seyfal<br>
  Babayev.  He was arrested by sanction of Parliament on November <br>
  5'95 for the organization of killing the  H.Aliyev's  supporter <br>
  in May 1990.<br>
     <br>
* November  25'95 - in the Prison Hospital in Boyuk Shor died the<br>
  Vice-Chairman   of   Social-democratic   Party,   teacher    of <br>
  Agricultural Academy Aypara Aliyev.  He was arrested on October <br>
  7'94 on the "October case."<br>
     <br>
* December 5'95 - in the Correcting Work Colony (ITK-12) died the<br>
  activist  of  PFA,  member of illegal military unit "Qaranqush" <br>
  Natiq Ahmedov.  He  was  sentenced  in  February  1995  to  the <br>
  13-years imprisonment for political killings.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Section 1</i><br>
<i>&gt;B. Disappearance</i><br>
<i>&gt;The Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan, a group connected to  the </i><br>
<i>&gt;Social Democratic Party, reports that...</i><br>
     <br>
HRCA is not affiliated or administrated by SDPA.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Section 1</i><br>
<i>&gt;C. Torture and other cruel,  inhuman,  or degrading treatment or </i><br>
<i>&gt;punishment</i><br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;In general,  access to regular prisons for foreign officials  is </i><br>
<i>&gt;not a problem; however, access to those held in security prisons </i><br>
<i>&gt;is denied.</i><br>
     <br>
Here is  only  one security prison,  an Investigation Isolator of <br>
Ministry of National Security.  Other  investigation  prisons  as <br>
well as  Correcting  Work  Colonies  is  common  for  the  people <br>
sentenced for the political and non-political crimes.<br>
     <br>
ICRC and journalists could visit in 1995  only  Armenians,  women <br>
and the people suffering by tuberculosis.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;D. Arbitrary arrest, detention, or exile</i><br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Various local  estimates  put  the  number  of   prisoners   and </i><br>
<i>&gt;detainees currently   under   arrest  on  politically  motivated </i><br>
<i>&gt;charges at 70 to 100.</i><br>
     <br>
Only after the attempt of coup d'etat in March 1995 were arrested <br>
for the treason of mother-land more than 500 people. Total number <br>
of imprisoneds for the political charges was in  1995  more  than <br>
800 people.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Azerbaijan does not practice forced exile.</i><br>
     <br>
But tens  of people were forced to escape from Azerbaijan because <br>
of real danger for their freedom,  health,  and lives. There is a <br>
practice of  forced  extradition  of  such kind of emigrants.  At <br>
least 13 political opponents were  extradited  to  Azerbaijan  in <br>
1995: 4 people from Russia, 4 from Ukraine, 5 from Georgia.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Section 2.</i><br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;D. Freedom of movement</i><br>
<i>&gt;There is  no  government  policy   of   discrimination   against </i><br>
<i>&gt;Armenians, who are free to travel.</i><br>
     <br>
Police always detains the  Armenians  who  try  to  escape  from <br>
Azerbaijan or  enter  to  it.  This  is  described  in the press, <br>
including the official one.<br>
     <br>
For example,<br>
* on  April  24, the  police detained in Baku Armenian woman Alya<br>
  Vanina-Kazarian who came from Russia;<br>
* in  May,  in Baku was detained Emil Paranian,  who lived in the<br>
  flat of his former wife;<br>
* in  late  June,  at  the border with Georgia,  in the train was<br>
  detained a resident of Baku,  Anahit Pashayeva who tried to  go <br>
  to Georgia;<br>
* in late July, at the Georgian border was detained a resident of<br>
  Ganja city, ethnic Armenian Maria Hasanova;<br>
* on December 26,  the ethnic Armenian woman, resident of Georgia<br>
  Sophia Safarova was detained by police.<br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;Section 5.</i><br>
     <br>
<i>&gt;The latter,  Turks  originally  from  the  Black  Sea  coast  of </i><br>
<i>&gt;Georgia, have  been  spread  throughout  Central  Asia  and  the </i><br>
<i>&gt;Caucasus, and want to return to their original motherland.</i><br>
     <br>
Meskhetian Turks  never  live at the Black Sea coast,  but in the <br>
Samtskhe-Javakheti region  close  to  the  Turkish  and  Armenian <br>
borders.<br>
     <br>
     Eldar E. Zeynalov,<br>
     Director<br>
     Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan.<br>
     <br>
<p>
The form of full name of Azeris is (1st name) (Patronimic)+ oglu<br>
(Surname), for example: Nariman Yaman oglu Yahyayev.<br>
