<title>Human Rights Center of Azerbaijan: Review of Political Arrests and Trials in Azerbaijan</title>
<h1>Review of Political Arrests and Trials in Azerbaijan</h1>
Anthony Galietti (<i>agaliett</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 16 Aug 96 09:37:50 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#17">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#17">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#17">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#17">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0018.html">Anthony Galietti: "List of Political Prisoners in Azerbaijan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0016.html">agalietti@sorosny.org: "Comments to the US State Dept country report 1995"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<br>
              HUMAN RIGHTS CENTER OF AZERBAIJAN                <br>
 3-11,28th May St.,Baku 370014,Azerbaijan;tel/fax (8922)987555 <br>
            E-mail RELCOM: eldar@hrcenter.baku.az              <br>
                    = November 14, 1995 =                      <br>
<br>
<p>
           POLITICAL ARRESTS AND TRIALS IN AZERBAIJAN<br>
                   (June 1993 - November 1995)<br>
<p>
     After the change of Azerbaijan leadership in June  1993  the<br>
political prisoners of old regime were released and began the new<br>
waves of arrests.  Reportedly,  to day in Azerbaijan are from 873<br>
to  894  prisoners  arrested  by the cases related with political<br>
struggles and terrorist  activity.  Among  them,  7  people  were<br>
arrested for  the  crimes  made in 1992,  70-84 people - in 1993,<br>
270-282 - of 1994 and 510-513 people - in 1995.<br>
     Only 24  from the detained people were sentenced in 1994 and<br>
192 - in 1995.  There are the arrested members of Popular  Front,<br>
"Musavat", Labour,  "Boz Qurd", "Chagdash Turan", Social-democra-<br>
tic and, probably, Popular Democratic Parties.<br>
     The main political arrests and trials are since June 1993 as<br>
follows:<br>
<p>
              "Nakhichevan case" of October 1992<br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     When the  incumbent President Heydar Aliyev was a Speaker of<br>
local  Parliament  (Ali  Medjlis)  of  Nakhichevanian  Autonomous<br>
Republic (NAR) and Popular Front (PFA) came to the power in Baku,<br>
the activists  of  local  branch of PFA made on October 24'92 the<br>
unsuccessful attempt of local coup d'etat.  The Procurator  began<br>
the  investigation  in  July 1993,  when Aliyev became the acting<br>
President of Azerbaijan.<br>
     After 2,5   years   seven  oppositioners  were sentenced  to<br>
different terms of imprisonment on charge of this coup d'etat:<br>
     Huseynov Fatulla, 5 years;<br>
     Mahmudov Vidadi, 5 years;<br>
     Mammedov Rahib, 7 years;<br>
     Mustafayev Siyavush, 8 years;<br>
     Quliyev Asaf, 9 years;<br>
     Qurbanov Faxraddin, 7 years;<br>
     Safarov Ibrahim, 5 years.<br>
Total number of prisoners on this case is 7 people.<br>
<p>
             "The Armenian terror cases", 1992-1995<br>
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Six Russian military servicemen, who helped the Armenians in<br>
their operations  in  Karabakh  war and surrendered to Azerbaijan<br>
authorities on  September  11'92,  were  sentensed  to  death  (5<br>
people) and 15 years (1 man) and given to Russian authorities  on<br>
September 23'93.<br>
     The correspondent  of  newspaper  "Demokratichesiy  Tilzit",<br>
citizen of Russia,  Igor Khatkovskiy was arrested on August  6'93<br>
in  Baku  and centenced to 8-years imprisonment on July 22'94 for<br>
spying (Art.58 of CC),  disersion (Art.68) and illegal custody of<br>
explosive substance (Art.220, part 2).<br>
     Other Russian  citizen,  Vassiliy  Lougovoy was sentenced to<br>
death on November 1994 by Military Collegium of Supreme Court for<br>
the diversions  (Art.61).  He served in Armenian Armed forces and<br>
mined the frontier zone in Fuzuli district,  where in result were<br>
killed 2 Azerbaijani frontier officers.<br>
     The Russian   citizens   Saakov   Kamo  Fyodorovich  (ethnic<br>
Armenian), his wife Saakova Irina Alexandrovna and Ilchuk Anatoly<br>
Anatolievich were arrested on July 1994 in the forrest near  Oguz<br>
town and  accused in the preparation of diversion in Baku subway.<br>
On August 1995 Saakov was sentenced to death,  and  Ilchuk  -  to<br>
15-years  imprisonment  for  the  articles  15,61 (preparation of<br>
diversion),  71 (contraband) and 220 (illegal custody of weapon).<br>
On this  case were arrested also Artur Arutiunov,  Tarlan Jafarov<br>
and Alexander Kolesnikov,  whose cases were investigated to begin<br>
of August 1995.<br>
     As stated  the  Minister of National Security Namiq Abbasov,<br>
also ten people were arrested on the case  of  the  explosion  in<br>
Baku Metro  in  March  1994  and the invistigation ended in early<br>
October 1995.  Eleventh  terrorist  died   immediately   in   the<br>
explosion.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 17 people.<br>
<p>
                 The defamation cases of 1992-95<br>
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Miralim Bahramov,  the leader of PFA activists in Djalilabad<br>
district, was  arrested  on  October  1992  for the defamation of<br>
President Elchibey.  The  accusation  was  later changed  to  the<br>
organization of  illegal  armed  group  and  attempt  of  illegal<br>
meeting. He was released in begin of July 1993.<br>
     The PFA  leader  in  Agdash district Maherram Mehraliyev was<br>
arrested  on  September  15'93  for  the  defamation  of   acting<br>
President Heydar Aliyev, but on February 15'94 was sentenced to 3<br>
years of imprisonment for the illegal custody of weapon.  He  was<br>
released on April 16'95 after 19 months of imprisonment.<br>
     The famous historian Movsum Aliyev was arrested on  December<br>
1994 also for the defamation of acting President Heydar Aliyev on<br>
September  1993  by  his  article  in  the oppositional newspaper<br>
"Azadliq". M.Aliyev was released only on February 18'95 after the<br>
President  said  in  Parliament,  that he did not know about this<br>
event and have not some pretension to him.<br>
     Four people were arrested on March 1995 for one  cartoon  in<br>
the illegal  satirical newspaper "Cheshma":<br>
     Ahmedov Ayaz Ahmed  oglu,  1962,  teacher,  journalist  (ANI<br>
Agency,  Russia),  Ahmedov Asgar Sujaet oglu (Asgar Ahmed), 1957,<br>
teacher,  politician ("Musavat" Party), Bayramov Malik Shamsaddin<br>
oglu, journalist ("Cumhuriyyet" newspaper), Mamedli Yadigar Tarix<br>
oglu, journalist ("Cumhuriyyet" newspaper).<br>
     Later was  arrested  also  Zeynalov  Mirzahuseyn  Shahhuseyn<br>
oglu, independent distributor of press and the worker of "Gunesh"<br>
printing-house Yaman Abbasov.<br>
     It was recognized as insulting the honor and dignity of  the<br>
President (Art.188-6,  part 2 of Crime Code).  The trial began in<br>
Baku City Court on June 22'95 and ended on October 19'95  by  the<br>
sentences of 2-5 years imprisonment.  The President amnested them<br>
on November 11'95.<br>
     On September 5'95 the Bilasuvar regional procurator informed<br>
the Chairman of Social-democratic Party,  MP Araz  Alizade  about<br>
the  begin  of his criminal case.  The accusation is that Alizade<br>
criticized the internal politics of President on May 20'95 before<br>
displaced people in Bilasuvar tent camp (Art.188-6, p.1). Because<br>
of his MP immunity,  the investigation was not made.  The term of<br>
immunity was till November 12'95.<br>
<p>
              "The cases of Sadvalists", 1993-1994<br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Five citizens  of  Russia,  activists  of  Lezghi   National<br>
movement "Sadval" were arrested on March 26'93 in Yalama Station,<br>
Khachmaz district,  when they had transported a  weapon.  All  of<br>
them were released on October 1993.<br>
     On April  1993 in Khachmaz and Qusar districts were arrested<br>
additionally at least 6 person,  who were sympathetic to ideas of<br>
"Sadval":  Abdullayev Faxraddin Abdulla oglu (was released before<br>
June 24'93),  Hadjiyev Agasamed,  Rustamov Sultan Shahmurad  oglu<br>
(was   arrested   on  March  31'93  and  sentenced  to  6  months<br>
imprisonment),  Kasumov  Surxay  Shahefi  oglu,  Sheydayev  Elxan<br>
Yadullayevich.<br>
     According the information of "Sadval",  to  Spring  1993  in<br>
imprisonment  are  26  activists of this organization and for the<br>
present all of them were probably released.<br>
     Migraliyev Nabi Shikhaliyevich, born 1960, citizen of Russia<br>
and activist of "Sadval",  was  arrested  on  September  3'94  in<br>
Azerbaijan for organizing the illegal meeting in Saur settlement,<br>
Qusar district on November 24'93.  According the  information  of<br>
his  relatives,  he  was  sentenced  without  advocat on December<br>
22'94. The sentence is unknown.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 1 man.<br>
<p>
                   "Gandja Case" of June 4'93<br>
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The attempt of the government of Popular Front to disarm the<br>
half-legal military unit #709 in Gandja City resulted in 35  died<br>
and hundreds wounded people and victory of rebels.<br>
     Five officials are now accused  in  using  the  armed  force<br>
against people, i.e. the high treason:<br>
1. Akberov Sulhaddin,  former First Deputy Minister  of  National<br>
   Security<br>
2. Allahverdiyev  Abdulla, former Minister of Interior<br>
3. Qambar Isa, former Chairman of Supreme Soviet<br>
4. Mammedov  Qabil,  former  First  Deputy  Minister  of Interior<br>
   (escaped from the court hall)<br>
5. Rzayev Dadash, former Minister of Defense<br>
6. Shirinov Ixtiyar, former General Procurator<br>
7. Tahmazov Faxraddin, former Minister of National Security<br>
     The trial  began on April 26'94 under the hidden suppression<br>
of Prime-Minister Suret Huseynov, former head of Ganja rebellion.<br>
After the  attempt  of new coup d'etat made S.Huseynov October in<br>
Ganja in October 1994,  he was discharged and escaped. Since this<br>
time the  trial became passive,  and the sentence on January 9'95<br>
was to remit the case for further inquiry.<br>
     The cases  of some former officials involved in Ganja events<br>
are investigating separately. For example, former Deputy Minister<br>
of  Justice,  colonel  Mammed  Zeynalov  was arrested on November<br>
18'93 and sentensed on August 3'94 for the illegal  detaining  of<br>
rebels. Now he is freed.<br>
     Former Commandant  of  Internal Forces of MIA Fahmin Hadjiev<br>
was arrested on May 24'94.  Last accusations were on the articles<br>
15,  94 (p.6), 255 "a", "c", 245 "d", 255-1 "a" and 238, and were<br>
not related with Ganja events.  The Military  Tribunal  sentenced<br>
him on August 7'95 to 10-years imprisonment.<br>
     Former Minister of Agriculture Tofiq Huseynov, who attempted<br>
to  organize the resistance to rebels,  was arrested on May 25'94<br>
and sentenced on October 26'94 to 2 years  imprisonment  for  the<br>
illegal custody of weapon. For the present he is freed.<br>
     Former Chief of Qazax District  Police  Isaxan  Ashurov  was<br>
arrested on September 23'94 for the resistanse to rebels in Qazax<br>
and sentensed by Gandja City Court to 2 years of forced work.<br>
     Some former Heads of District  Executive  Authorities  (DEA)<br>
were  reportedly  arrested  with violation of law procedure.  For<br>
example,  former Head of Jebrayil DEA,  Elxan Subhanverdiyev  was<br>
arrested  on  July  1993 in Sumqayit City and detained in Bayilov<br>
prison till December 1993. In Autumn 1993 was reportedly arrested<br>
also the Head of Qubatli DEA Aydin Shukurov.<br>
     After the  change  of  the  government  in  Autumn 1994 were<br>
arrested 4 people who  killed  the  Procurator  of  Samux  region<br>
Shimshir  Aliyev on June 7'93 during the rebellion.  The case was<br>
submitted to the court.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 7-8 people.<br>
<p>
             "Lenkaran Case" of June 14-August 23'93<br>
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The armed group of the "military opposition" claimed on June<br>
24'93 the  "Talish-Mugan  Autonomous Republic" in the 6 districts<br>
on South.  During the suppressing of this movement were killed  3<br>
people.<br>
     There were  accused  in  the non-political crimes 23 people.<br>
For today 2 from them were condemned conditionally  and  released<br>
on Spring 1994:<br>
     Huseynov Dashdamir Shirinali oglu,<br>
     Nurullayev Djeyhun Teyyub oglu.<br>
     One from  arrested,  former  "President  of  TMAR"   Alakram<br>
Hummatov escaped  from  the Investigation Isolator of Ministry of<br>
National Security on September 1994.  He was found  and  arrested<br>
again  only on August 3'95.  The others are under the trial began<br>
in Military Collegium of Supreme Court on February 6'94:<br>
     Akberov Kamran  Qurban  oglu,  Aliyev  Rafaddin Rahman oglu,<br>
     Asadullayev Ilham Saleh oglu,  Bagirov Nadir  Israfil  oglu,<br>
     Djafarov Elshan Dashdamir oglu, Hadjiyev Baxtiyar Hadjiverdi<br>
     oglu, Hadjiyev  Jebrayil  Hadjiverdi  oglu,  Hadjiyev Mikail<br>
     Hadjiverdi oglu,  Huseynov  Qudrat  Iltifat  oglu,  Huseynov<br>
     Ramiq   Baldadash   oglu,  Huseynov  Sahib  Baldadash  oglu,<br>
     Ismayilov Aflatun  Ibrahim  oglu,  Kalantarli  Asaf  Israfil<br>
     oglu,  Kerimov Zulfuqar Alekber oglu, Mammedov Nayib Bahadur<br>
     oglu,  Nasirov Ali Qurban oglu,  Qurbanov Ajdar Mammed oglu,<br>
     Rahimov  Arif  Mashalla  oglu,  Sadiqov  Djavanshir Diyashar<br>
     oglu, Xalilov Sulduz Ibrahim oglu.<br>
There was information also about the possible arrests of  Abbasov<br>
Qadir, Qasimov Hokmulla, Qasimov Mikail, and Quliyev Isbat.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 19-23 people.<br>
<p>
                "Qaranqush" case of August 31'93<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Till the occupation of Qubadli district by  Armenians  there<br>
was the  volunteer  group  "Qaranqush" ("Swallow") established by<br>
local branch of PFA. Reportedly, they killed some local officials<br>
on August 31'93 during the battle for Qubatli district. On Autumn<br>
1993 the members of "Qaranqush" were arrested  in  Sumqayit  city<br>
(one fighter was killed, the other one made a suicyde).<br>
     In begin of May  1995  eight  members  of  "Qaranqush"  were<br>
sentenced on charge of killings and gangsterism:<br>
     Ahmedov Namiq,  13  years,  Asadov  Rovshan,  death,  Asadov<br>
Seymur, 12 years, Jabiyev Samandar, 15 years, Mammedaliyev Sahib,<br>
death,   Mikailov  Jeyhun,  12  years,  Qayibov  Intiqam,  death,<br>
Shahmuradov Yashar, death.<br>
     The brothers Guloglan and Novruz Novruzov  died  during  the<br>
investigation term, and I.Qayibov made 2 attempts of suicyde.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 8 people.<br>
<p>
                  "Terror case" of October 1'93<br>
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The group   of  supporters  of  President  Abulfaz  Elchibey<br>
planned the  killing  of  Chairman  of  Supreme  Soviet,   acting<br>
President Heydar  Aliyev  on  October  1'93.  In  this  case were<br>
involved the citizen of Turkey Hasan  Toku  Saleh  Zaki  oglu  as<br>
direct killer,  the cousin of Elchibey Aydin Qasimov and some PFA<br>
activists.<br>
     The trial  was in Baku from March 1 to 12'94.  The sentences<br>
are as follows:<br>
     Babayev Abil Suleyman oglu - 12 years,<br>
     Hasan Toku Saleh Zaki oglu - 10 years,<br>
     Qasimov Aydin Madat oglu - 12 years<br>
of imprisonment with detaining in the Colony  of  Strong  Regime.<br>
Two defendant,  Nariman Mammedov and Ali Asgarov were  reportedly<br>
released  on the bail.  Sahib Huseynov,  Bayram Ahmedov and Fazil<br>
Kerimov were are hidden from the investigation.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 3-5 people.<br>
<p>
              "Nakhichevan case" of October 29'93<br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Since the President of Azerbaijan, Chairman of Popular Front<br>
Abulfaz Elchibey had escaped from capital to the NAR,  the  local<br>
opposition became  more  active.  On October 29'93 in Nakhichevan<br>
City the supporters of Elchibey attempted to take the building of<br>
Ministry  of  Internal  Affairs  of  NAR.  It  was the reason for<br>
mass arrests of oppositioners in NAR.<br>
     The first  trial  by  this  case  began  on  March 29'94 and<br>
finished on May 25'94. There were sentenced 5 members of PFA:<br>
     Jahangirov Rashid,  2  years  of  imprisonment,   Mustafayev<br>
Siyavush,  4 years,  Mamishov Javad, 2 years, Mirzaliyev Vaqif, 2<br>
years, Veliyev Anar, 2 years.<br>
     There are probably also  other trials, because was published<br>
the information about some sentenced supporters PFA:<br>
     Asadov Veli Huseyn oglu,  was on June'94 sentenced to 1 year<br>
of imprisonment  in  Bayilov  prison,  Djafarov  Araz,  6  years,<br>
Mustafayev  Shahin,  1  year,  Ramazanov Ilham,  5 years,  Rzayev<br>
Rashid, 2,5 years, Seyidov Mirhasan, 2 (or 4) years.<br>
     There was sentenced on other trial  also  Mustafayev  Sattar<br>
Mustafa  oglu  (arrested  on January 22'94,  sentenced to 6-years<br>
imprisonment)<br>
     However, they  are  not only arrested by this case,  because<br>
reportedly were arrested more than  20  people.  The  some  known<br>
names of arrested on November 1993 - January 1994 are:<br>
     Abbasov Ibrahim,  Abdullayev Yaqub,  Agayev  Nazim,  Akberov<br>
Izzet, Aliyev Orudj, Azimoglu (Ashrafoglu) Ilyas, Babayev Huseyn,<br>
Heydarov Qurbanali,  Huseynov Nariman,  Huseynov Ramiz, Ismayilov<br>
Alasgar,  Kazimov  Ilham,  Mammedov  Intiqam,  Qasimov Djabrayil,<br>
Quliyev Bashir, Sharurlu Yaqub, Suleymanov Qurban.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case  is  29  people  (one<br>
from them was sentenced on other case, too).<br>
<p>
                "Sheki case" of November 16-17'93<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Eight activists of Islam Society "Yeni Azeri" were  arrested<br>
on November 17'93 on charge  of  hooliganism  after  the  illegal<br>
meetings were organized by them in Sheki City.<br>
     The Sheki  district court sentenced the all on January 17'95<br>
to different terms of imprisonment.  Five of them  were  released<br>
and 3 are detained in colony (ITK).<br>
     It's known only one name:  Salimov Mammedemin,  the Chairman<br>
of "Yeni Azeri".<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 3 people.<br>
<p>
                "Beylaqan case" of December 16'93<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Seven oppositioners  were  arrested  on  December  16'93  in<br>
Beylaqan district on charge of diversion activity:<br>
     Abishov Ilham,  Mammedov  Soltan,  Mammedov Teyyar,  Nasirov<br>
Ismayil, Quliyev Aladdin, Quliyev Eivaz (the all are activists of<br>
PFA),  Alishov  Arif  (the  Chair  of  local  branch  of  Popular<br>
Democratic Party of Azerbaijan).<br>
     There is not information about their further fate.<br>
Total number of possible prisoners on this case is 7 people.<br>
<p>
                  The Ordubad cases, 1994-1995<br>
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Ordubad region,  where  is  located  the   head-quarter   of<br>
ex-President of  Azerbaijan,  Chairman  of  Popular  Front  Party<br>
Abulfaz Elchibey,  is accounted as  the  area  of  illegal  armed<br>
groups of PFP supporters.<br>
     On May  9'94  in Ordubad was happened the illegal meeting of<br>
PF supporters,  ended by the mass  disorders  and  struggle  with<br>
police. On  June  4'94  the illegal armed group located in Ustupu<br>
village attacked the building of regional police. On August 30'94<br>
this armed  group  take  in  the  siege  the  building  of  local<br>
Executive Power and organized the  illegal  meeting.  On  January<br>
28'95 several  policemen  were  disarmed  by this group in Vanand<br>
village.<br>
     One of PFP leaders,  MP Faraj Quliyev was arrested on August<br>
29'95 in Ordubad as the organiser of all of these actions. He was<br>
accused  on  the  articles 70 (banditry),  70-2 (establishment of<br>
illegal armed groups), 72 (organization of mass disorders), 188-3<br>
(mass actions,  violating the social order), 189-1 (resistance to<br>
policeman). The Parliament agreed with arrest on August  30.  His<br>
trial started in early October 1995 in Nakhchivan city.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 1 people.<br>
<p>
                  "Qusar case" of June 14-15'94<br>
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     After the police killed 1 man and wounded 1 man in the Piral<br>
village, Qusar district,  the local people organized the  illegal<br>
meeting and   attacked  the  buildings  of  District  Police  and<br>
Executive Authority.  There were arrested some people,  including<br>
the leader of local PFA branch R.Salimov.<br>
     On November  21'94  3 people were sentenced on the charge of<br>
organizing the disorders (Art.72 of CC):<br>
     Bakarov Rasim, 3 years imprisonment,<br>
     Damirov Fikret, 2 years imprisonment,<br>
     Salimov Rauf, 3 years imprisonment,<br>
with detaining in Corrective Work's Colony (ITK).<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 3 people.<br>
<p>
                "Sharur case" of August 28-29'94<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The central  government  disarmed  in  Sharur  district  the<br>
illegal military unit of the PFA supporters.  After the fightings<br>
on August  28-29'94  in Sharur,  Ordubad and Djulfa districts and<br>
Nakhichevan City were reportedly arrested 25-29  people,  9  from<br>
them after  their  voluntary  disarmament.  There  are some known<br>
names:<br>
     Abdullayev Ilyas   (Deputy   of  Supreme  Medjlis  of  NAR),<br>
Abdullayev Mubariz (Oglanqala village,  Sharur district), Akberov<br>
Israfil  Isa  oglu  (Yuxari Dasharx village,  Sharur d.),  Aliyev<br>
Ismayil Farman oglu (Sharur district),  Aliyev Niftali Allahverdi<br>
oglu (Xaladj village,Sharur district), Aliyev Siyafar Djalal oglu<br>
(Chomaqtur  village,  Sharur  district),  Allahverdiyev   Faramaz<br>
(Deputy  of  Supreme Medjlis of NAR),  Asgarov Allahverdi (Sharur<br>
City,  Director of  Museum),  Axundov  Fuad  Djavad  oglu  (Yayci<br>
village,  Sharur  district),  Axundov  Ismayil  Ali  oglu  (Yayci<br>
village,  Sharur district),  Djalalov Shahin Djalal oglu  (Yuxari<br>
Dasharx, Sharur district),  Farzaliyev Teyyub (?), Huseynov Tahir<br>
(Sharur district),  Mammedov Rovshan Djamil oglu  Nagiyev  Huseyn<br>
(Sharur district),  Nagiyev Ibrahim (?), Qaziyev Sabir Hamza oglu<br>
(Sharur  district),  Quliyev Vidadi Heydar oglu (Yengide village,<br>
Sharur  district),  Rzayev  Vilayet  (Sharur  district),  Seyidov<br>
Mirqasim  (Oglanqala village,  Sharur district),  Talibov Shirzad<br>
Ali oglu (1949,Siyaqut  village,Sharur  district),  Veliyev  Musa<br>
(Sadarak district), Zamanli Ali (Sharur district).<br>
     All of them are the members of PFA, excluding A.Asgarov, who<br>
is a member of "Musavat" Party.  In the end of October 1994  they<br>
were detained in Investigation Isolator of MIA of NAR.<br>
     The Parliament  of  Azerbaijan agreed to arrest of leader of<br>
this group,  MP Shakhmardan (Shahsultan) Mahammad oglu Jafarov on<br>
May 30'95. He escaped from arrest a long time, and was wounded on<br>
June  17'95  in  Julfa  district  and  died on June 29 in the MIA<br>
hospital in Baku.<br>
     During this  police  operation  were  arrested   5   people,<br>
including wounded  Sh.Jafarov  and  Bagirov  Anver  Bagir  oglu.<br>
Reportedly, later was arrested also PFA activist  Hatam  Nabiyev,<br>
who tried to visit the wounded colleague in Nakhchivani hospital.<br>
     After the arrest of Jafarov, in Julfa district were arrested<br>
on June  21'95  also  Vice-Chairmen  of Nakhchivani branch of PFA<br>
Faraj Yusifbeyli and Huseyn Javadov,  and the member of "Chagdash<br>
Turan" Party  Oqtay  Dashoguz.  On  June  22'95  in  Sharur  were<br>
arrested 4 people from the Jafarov's unit.<br>
     The trial  on the case of 19 defendants from Sharur would be<br>
began on June 25'95 in Nakhchivan City.<br>
     As was   known,   the   trial   on   the  case  of  arrested<br>
F.Allahverdiyev (#6) began on June 27.  He was accused  on  other<br>
crimes  on  the  articles  188-3 (organizing the mass disorders),<br>
189-1 (resistance to policeman) and  207  (hooliganism).  As  the<br>
sample  of his hooliganism,  was mentioned outrage upon the Lenin<br>
memorial in Nakhchivan City.  The sentence passed in  July'95  is<br>
2,5-years imprisonment.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 20-32 people.<br>
<p>
              Case of Ali Kerimov (September 10'94)<br>
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     During the arrests of participants of illegal meeting of PFA<br>
in Baku on September 10'94 was arrested also Vice-Chairman of PFA<br>
for the  politics Ali Kerimov.  Police searched him and found one<br>
hand-granade. On September 14'94 was began the case on charge  of<br>
illegal custody of weapon (Art.220-1 of Crime Code).  Kerimov was<br>
released on  September  14'94,  but the closed case was re-opened<br>
again on May 27'95.<br>
<p>
     "The case of escape from Prison of MNS" on September 21'94<br>
     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     On September 21'94 four state criminals - Alakram  Hummatov,<br>
Rahim Qaziyev,  Baba  Nazarli  and Arif Pashayev escaped from the<br>
Investigation Isolator of Ministry of  National  Security  ("SIZO<br>
MNB") in Baku.  Reportedly,  it was organized by the officials of<br>
MNS. To day are arrested 5 people:<br>
1.Alishov Rizvan Rushan oglu, Controller of SIZO,<br>
2.Babayev Musa Vaqif oglu, Controller of SIZO,<br>
3.Imranov Nariman Shamo oglu, former Minister of National Security,<br>
4.Radjabov Radjab  Yusif  oglu,  Controller  of  SIZO,<br>
5.Mirzoyev Faiq Agaxanoglu, orderly officer.<br>
     Imranov is accused on the articles  57,  part  1;  255  'b';<br>
17-185, part 2; 193, part 2; 185-3 of Crime Code, the others - on<br>
the art. 255 "b", 17-185, part 2, 185-3.<br>
     On June  1995  was  known about ending the investigation and<br>
submitting this case to Supreme Court.  But trial didn't start in<br>
the  usual  term (on July 25'95),  probably,  because of catching<br>
Mirzoyev on  August  3'95  in  Lenkaran  city,  together  escaped<br>
prisoner A.Hummatov.<br>
     In Lenkaran were arrested on August  3-6'95  Aliaga  Ibadov,<br>
Rovshan   Quliyev,   Farman   Hummatov,  Nariman  Hummatov,  Miri<br>
Dadashov,  Seyidaga  Dadashov  (shortly),  Yusif  Rasulov,  Jamal<br>
Kazimov,   Sakit   Murshudov,   Yasanaga  Isganderov,  Shamseddin<br>
Abdullayev, Alasaf Mahmudov, Rahim Mammedov, Safayil Mammedov.<br>
     Two people more,  Qaziyev's brother Rahib Qaziyev and Deputy<br>
Director of Xirdalan Milk Factory Elxan Abbasov, were arrested on<br>
August 9'95  on  this  case.  On  August  13  were  arrested also<br>
Rahimov's cousins  Farda  and  Mammed   Qaziyevs,   and   fellow-<br>
countrymen -  the  Chairman  of the "Ocaq" Society,  Sheki region<br>
Nasib Muxtarov and his son-in-law (his  name  was  not  written).<br>
Rahimov's uncle, Sabir Rahimov was arrested in early October 1995.<br>
     Rahim Qaziyev  himself  is  for  the  present  in  political<br>
emigration in Russia. Baba Nazarli, who also lived there, died on<br>
January 29'95. Arif Pashayev, who returned to the trial after the<br>
Parliament  warranted his security,  was arrested again on August<br>
13'95.<br>
     The case of 5 officials of MNS,  A.Hummatov  and  A.Pashayev<br>
is investigated and passed to the Supreme Court on November 7'95.<br>
     Among the escapeds from the arrest the president  of  Talish<br>
Cultural  Center  Saadat  Xalilov,  president of "Avesta" Society<br>
Zahiraddin Ibrahimov and Chairwoman of Committee  for  Protecting<br>
the Rights of Talish Women Sudaba Rasulova (Hummatov's wife).<br>
     According the  President  Aliyev's  words,  the total number<br>
arrested in Lenkaran, Baku and Sheki for the helping Hummatov and<br>
Qaziyev is  40  people  (this  number was confirmed in the public<br>
speech of Procurator General Eldar Hasanov on November 9'95).<br>
<p>
                "Terror case" of September 29'94<br>
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     On September 29'94 in Baku were killed the Vice-chairman  of<br>
Supreme  Soviet  of Azerbaijan Afiyaddin Jalilov and the Chief of<br>
Special Administration of President Shamsi Ragimov.  On this case<br>
were arrested  3  policemen  from the Special Police Unit (OPON),<br>
including the driver of District Procurator Mahir  Javadov.  That<br>
was the reason of disorders of OPON in Baku from September 30  to<br>
October 4'94.<br>
     The terrorists,  who  were  arrested  in October 1995,  are:<br>
Aliyev Elchin Qaraoglan oglu,  DOB 1969, member of OPON; Muxtarov<br>
Fazil  Famil  oglu,  DOB  1971,  member  of OPON;  Huseynov Fazil<br>
Zulfuqar oglu, DOB 1962, former policeman.<br>
     Total number of prisoners on this case is 3 people.<br>
<p>
             "Gandja (October) case" of October 4'94<br>
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The armed  group  of the supporters of former Prime-Minister<br>
Suret Huseynov attempted on October 4'94 to make coup  d'etat  in<br>
Gandja City.  By  last  official  reports  of  Procurator General<br>
(April and November 1995),  there were killed 3,  wounded  4  and<br>
arrested 203 people. Also 66 people are in the search.<br>
     The "October case" in the whole is not finally investigated,<br>
and arrests are continuing.  During 7 months the total number  of<br>
the  arresteds id increased from 180 to 203 people.  Some of them<br>
escaped  to  Russia,  but  the  mutual  agreement  on  the  legal<br>
cooperation made possible their arrest. So, on May 1995 in Russia<br>
was arrested and passed to Azerbaijan one of main  organisers  of<br>
October  Putsch,  Nusret  Budaqov.  He  died in the Investigation<br>
Prison of MNS on July 10'95.  In late October 1995  was  arrested<br>
Ilqar Safixanov,  who lived in Moscow on the false documents. Now<br>
is discussed the problem of his passing to Azerbaijan.<br>
     To day to the Supreme Court  were  given  59  cases  of  186<br>
people, and already 81 people were sentenced  on  the  20  cases.<br>
Some of them are known to HRCA:<br>
     "Minqechevir case"   (April-May   1995):   12  residents  of<br>
Minqechevir City planned  to  support  the  Gandja  rebellion  on<br>
October 4'94.  There were sentenced on the charge in high treason<br>
(art.57 of Crime Code) the following people: Amirov Mahyaddin (to<br>
5-years  imprisonment),  Bagirov Bagir Agali oglu,  Chief of City<br>
Administration for Exploitation of  Houses  (12  years),  Eynalov<br>
Fariz Eldar oglu,  bodyguard of Ali Yahyayev (10 years),  Hasanov<br>
Mushfiq Mikayil oglu (10 years),  Hasanov Mushfiq Nusret oglu (10<br>
years),  Mammedov  Mammedjan Ali oglu,  1958,  worker (10 years),<br>
Nagiyev Elshan Zameddin oglu  (10  years),  Qarayev  Aqil  Soltan<br>
oglu,  Chief  of Building Administration #62 (11 years),  Qarayev<br>
Sahavat Bagi oglu (10 years),  Rasulov  Shahruyya  Alistan  oglu,<br>
1953,  Deputy of Minqechevir City Soviet (10 years), Yahyayev Ali<br>
Safarli oglu,  former Chief of  Department  of  City  police  (12<br>
years),  Yahyayev  Nariman  Yaman  oglu,  1952,  former  Chief of<br>
Department of City police,  was arrested  on  December  6'94  (10<br>
years).<br>
     On June 16'95,  on the one of Gandja episodes were sentenced<br>
10 people.  Among them are: Rafiyev Elchin, sentenced to 13-years<br>
imprisonment, Novruzov Xaqani - to 11 years, Hasanov Akif - to 12<br>
years,  and  others,  whose  names  are  unknown,  sentenced   to<br>
different terms.<br>
     In July'95 in the court were given the case of 32 members of<br>
"Committee for protection of shehid's (i.e.  died  for  the  just<br>
cause)  families  "Nicat" ('Salvation'),  who were accused in the<br>
attempt of coup d'etat on October 4'94,  establishment of illegal<br>
armed  group,  detaining  the  innocent  people under the arrest,<br>
using the violence against them,  embezzlement of the state funds<br>
in special big volumes,  and also in the criminal actions,  which<br>
had the human victims as their result. The articles of accusation<br>
bill are 57 (p.1),  65,  70 (p.2),  220-1,  243 etc. of the Crime<br>
Code of Azerbaijani Republic.  There was mentioned only one  name<br>
of Vaqif Meshadiqara oglu Hamidov.<br>
     The second case given to the court in July 1995 is the  case<br>
of Veliyev Rashid, Artyuk Vasily and Shirinov Azer.<br>
     On July 20'95 were sentenced also Nagiyev  Elxan  (14  years<br>
term),  Abbasov  Zakir  (13  years),  Agamirov Elshad (13 years),<br>
Aslanov Afaq (12 years),  Ahmedov Aladdin (11 years) and  also  3<br>
people (10 years).<br>
     Case of the former Military Comissar of Nizami  District  of<br>
Ganja  city,  colonel  Hamzayev Firudin Nariman oglu,  colonel in<br>
reserve Aslanov Ilham  Ismayil  oglu  and  colonel  Madatov  Alik<br>
Hadjibala oglu was given to the Supreme Court in August 1995.<br>
     Case of Aliyev Jafar Rza oglu and his son Aliyev Ilqar Jafar<br>
oglu,  residents  of Uchtepe village,  Xanlar region was given to<br>
the Supreme Court in August 1995.<br>
     Case of Aliyev Aypara Nasreddin oglu, a teacher of the State<br>
Agricultural Academy was given to the  Supreme  Court  in  August<br>
1995, but prisoner died on November 25'95.<br>
     In September  1995,  the  investigation  was finished on the<br>
case of former Chief of the Artillery Department of  Ministry  of<br>
Defense Mammedov  Hadjiragim  Samed oglu (articles of 57-1,  p.1;<br>
255 B;  220,  p.2 of Crime Code) and Chief of the  Department  of<br>
Ammunition of  the Armament Administration of DM Alekberov Eduard<br>
Niyaz oglu (art.  255 B).  On October 2'94 Mammedov commanded  to<br>
target the  cannons  to  the  buildings  of  Presidential  Staff,<br>
Parliament and DM, and Alekberov gave him 500 shells.<br>
     On October  2'95  began  the  trial  on  the  case of former<br>
Chief of the Military Police in Gandja city Eldar Aliyev.  He  is<br>
accused on   the   30  episodes,  including  "October  case"  and<br>
surrender of  Agdam city in Summer 1993.  In December 1995 Aliyev<br>
was sentenced  to   death,   Arzu   Ismayilov   -   to   11-years<br>
imprisonment, Araz Mammedov - to 12, two others - to 2 and 3.<br>
     The Supreme Court started in early November 1995  the  trial<br>
on  the  case  of  former  Chief of Baku Municipal Police Muradov<br>
Eldar.<br>
     In the press were mentioned the following names of arrested:<br>
Abdullayev Muzamil,  former Minister of Agriculture; Agayev Ayaz;<br>
Ahmedov Chapay,  Chief of State Way Police in Gandja; Amirahmedov<br>
Vuqar,  deserter;  Aliyev  Oqtay,  Senior  Referent  of Ministers<br>
Cabinet;  Babayev Telman, Chief of Qedabey District Department of<br>
Ministry of National Security;  Bagirov Kamil, Senior Referent of<br>
Ministers Cabinet; Budaqov Namiq, expert of Baku City Police, son<br>
of   Nusret   Budaqov,  former  Chairman  of  Charitable  Society<br>
"Nidjat"; Eyvazov Zahid; Hasanov Lankaran, Huseynov Shahin, Chief<br>
of  Investigation  Department  of  Gandja  City Police;  Huseynov<br>
Tahir;  Mammedov Qalib,  Senior Referent  of  Ministers  Cabinet;<br>
Musayev   Sardar,   former   Chief   of   Control  Department  of<br>
Agricultural Ministry;  Orudjov Ramil;  Qoshqarov Aytekin; Rzayev<br>
Ilqar;   Sadiqov   Vidadi,  earlier  sentenced;  Shamilov  Safar;<br>
Shamilov  Shamil,  Assistant  Prime-Minister;   Shirinov   Elman,<br>
Captain of Police,  Chief of Department of the fight against drug<br>
addiction  of  Gandja  City  Police;  Ukalayev  Ramazan,   Senior<br>
Referent of Ministers Cabinet;  Yaqubov Mohubbat; the former Head<br>
of Executive Authority (HEA) of Samux district Mammed Jalal  oglu<br>
Alekberov and former HEA of Xanlar district Sh.Abbasov.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is at least 203.<br>
<p>
               "Qazax-Agstafa Case" of March 13'95<br>
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The group of policemen  from  Special  Police  Unit  (OPON),<br>
local  policemen  and  civilians  attacked  the  buildings of the<br>
district police administrations in Qazax and  Agstafa  districts.<br>
They were  supported  by some civilians.  During the operation of<br>
disarmament were killed 6 people.<br>
     According the latest information of November 9'95 of General<br>
Procurator Eldar Hasanov,  there were arrested 293 people.  Among<br>
them  are  82-142  deserters,  60  OPON  members.  In August 1995<br>
E.Hasanov recognized before the Parliament that also 134 arrested<br>
people  were not guilty and now are liberated.<br>
     At least  130  from  them  were  accused  in  high   treason<br>
(Art.57-1 of  CC),  and  82 - in desertion.  The investigation is<br>
continued on the 6 cases of 170 people and finished on the  cases<br>
of 123  people.  Reportedly,  86 people were already sentenced to<br>
the end of August.<br>
     According the official report,  besides the members of  OPON<br>
and civilians  in  Qazax  were  arrested  also 8 local policemen:<br>
Alirzayev Maqsad Alirza oglu,  Captain;  Alirzayev Aqil Kommunist<br>
oglu,   policeman;   Isganderov   Seyid  Qeyis  oglu,  policeman;<br>
Ismayilov Ilqar Telman oglu,  policeman;  Mammedov Sahib Asadulla<br>
oglu,   policeman;  Suleymanov  Saleh  Ibrahim  oglu,  policeman;<br>
Xalilov Xalil Mahrali  oglu,  Colonel,  Chief  of  Qazax  police;<br>
Yunusov Huseyn Yaqub oglu, policeman.<br>
     The most  arresteds are detained in the Investigation Prison<br>
#2 in Gandja city.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 293 people.<br>
<p>
               "Baku March Case" of March 15-17'95<br>
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     In Baku  the Deputy Minister of Interior Rovshan Javadov and<br>
his brother  Mahir  Javadov  leaded  by  the rebellion of OPON on<br>
March 15-17'95.  Officially, there were killed 38-45 (including 7<br>
civilians) and wounded 105-117 people (48 civilians).<br>
     According the  latest  official report of Procurator General<br>
on November 9'95,  there were arrested 192 people,  including 130<br>
members  of  OPON,  35  civilians,  20  policemen  and 7 military<br>
servicemen. Besides that, 73 civilians sentenced administratively<br>
were  released because of protest of Procurator and 29 people are<br>
in the search.<br>
     In September  1995,  in  the  court  was  the case of Xanlar<br>
Aliyev,  Nizameddin Safarov,  Elchin Rustamov,  Musa Elvandov and<br>
others.<br>
     On other 6 episods are accused 60 people,  which  cases  are<br>
submitted to the court.<br>
     The legal  basis of arrests is the Decision of Milli Medjlis<br>
on March 22'95 "About the measures for the liquidation of attempt<br>
of coup  d'etat  and  the  strengthening  of  the State system in<br>
Azerbaijanian Republic".<br>
     The arrests  are  continued.  On  September  19'95,  in  the<br>
connection  with  March  events  was  arrested  MP,  activist  of<br>
"Musavat" Party Tofiq Qasimov.  Procurator General accused him in<br>
the ideological influence to the rebels (art.57 of Crime Code).<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 192 people.<br>
<p>
           The case of Isgandar Hamidov (March 17'95)<br>
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     The arrest of the Chairman of Azerbaijani "Boz Qurd"  Party,<br>
former Minister of Internal Affairs, MP Isgandar Hamidov on March<br>
17'95 was officially  related  with  March  events.  But  he  was<br>
accused on  the  Articles  88-1  (misappropriation  of  the state<br>
property in the big volume),  168,  part  1  and  2  (exceed  the<br>
powers). Reportedly,  other  8  members of the Party were shortly<br>
arrested.<br>
     Hamidov was   sentenced   in   September  1995  to  14-years<br>
imprisonment.<br>
     For the present the "Boz Qurd" Party is prohibited,  and the<br>
group of  its supporters created the National Democratic Party on<br>
its basis.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 1 people.<br>
<p>
               Case of "Ari" newspaper (June 7'95)<br>
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     Responsible Editor of "Ari" satirical newspaper Ilham Rzayev<br>
and  zonal  correspondent Telman Suleymanov were arrested on June<br>
7'94 on the charge of extorting the bribe (Art.170 of Azerbaijani<br>
Crime Code). They were arrested in the cabinet of First Deputy of<br>
Head of Masalli  Regional  Executive  Power  Ildirim  Allahyarov,<br>
where were assigned by Editor-in-Chief because of dissatisfaction<br>
of REP by one of articles in 'Ari'.<br>
     In September  1995 the journalists were sentenced by Masalli<br>
Regional Court to 8-years imprisonment.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 2 people.<br>
<p>
                   "Terror case of July 30'95"<br>
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     In the begin of August 1995 the authorities stated about new<br>
attempt to  the life of President Heydar Aliyev.  The National TV<br>
showed the mines founded on July 30 under one of the Baku bridges.<br>
     Reportedly, on the accusation in terror,  i.e. article 59 of<br>
the Crime Code were arrested 4 former members of  Special  Police<br>
Unit (OPON) and Director of  Little  Enterprise  "Polimer"  Ramiz<br>
Kerimov.  According  the  public  speech of Procurator General on<br>
November 9'95,  there were arrested 7 people  including  Mammedov<br>
Yashar Sabir  oglu,  related  with the rebellion of OPON in March<br>
1995).<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 7 people.<br>
<p>
             "Coup d'etat of Generals" (August 1995)<br>
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     According the officials,  this terror action was the part of<br>
attempt of coup d'etat,  preparing by  three  generals  and  some<br>
senior officers of Defense Ministry.<br>
     Three fighters were arrested  on  July  19'95  by  Ukrainian<br>
authorities. Two from generals, former Deputy Minister of Defense<br>
Vahid Musayev and former Commander of the Internal  Forces  Rafiq<br>
Agayev were arrested in early August 1995.  The third one, Shahin<br>
Musayev,  is living abroad and  has  the  Ukrainian  citizenship.<br>
There were  arrested  also colonel Jalal Mammedov and major Tahir<br>
Suleymanov.<br>
     In August  1995  were  arrested,  probably in the connection<br>
with this case,  the Chief of General Staff of DM Rasim  Muxtarov<br>
and former Chief of KGB Department Vladimir Mirzayev.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 7-9 people.<br>
<p>
        The arrests of supporters of Labour Party (1995)<br>
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
     On March  1995,  on  the  case  of  distributing  press   of<br>
opposition  Labour  Party of Azerbaijan was arrested the group of<br>
teachers of   Azerbaijani   Industrial  Institute:  Agayev  Ulduz<br>
(shortly), Chief of laboratory (was under the  arrest  10  days),<br>
Aliasgarov Ismayil, Balayev Vaqif (member of LPA).<br>
     Balayev was   sentenced   in  September  1995  to  7  months<br>
imprisonment and  released  a  few day later.  Aliasgarov,  which<br>
accusation was  changed  to  bribing,  got   the   2-years   term<br>
conditionally.<br>
     The second  wave  of  the  arrests  of  LPA  supporters   is<br>
reportedly related  by  their involving to the illegal custody of<br>
the weapon and terror cases of July  and  October  1995  and  the<br>
"Generals' Coup d'etat".  Reportedly, there was the plan to shoot<br>
down the plane of President by two missiles.<br>
     Among known  names are:  Hadjiyev Sabutay,  Chairman of LPA;<br>
Adigozalov Ibad,  one of the founders of LPA;  Aliyev Ahmed  Baba<br>
oglu;  Aliyev  Bayali  Xanali  oglu;  Aliyev  Mammedali;  Axundov<br>
Agaseyidmahammad (Aga)  Mirabdulqani  oglu,  former  Chairman  of<br>
"Qardashliq" Society;  Huseynov Huseynbala;  Rasulov Ali Mahammad<br>
oglu.  On this case was arrested also former commander  of  Agdam<br>
batallion of Special Police Unit (OPON) Faiq Bakhshaliyev.<br>
     Total number of arrested on this case is 8-9 people.<br>
<p>
     Director of HRCA                   Eldar Zeynalov.<br>
